const SEARCH_INDEX = [{"title": "Beast Master — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/beast-master/", "text": "Beast Master — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Beast Master B Class Guide Beast Master D Tier Role DPS Difficulty Easy Weapon Dual 1H Axes Contents Beast Master is currently in need of a rebalance. In its present state, the class is primarily used as a Rupee farmer. Check out the Rupee Farming Guide to learn how to make the most of it. Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Berserker — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/berserker/", "text": "Berserker — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Berserker B Class Guide Berserker B Tier Role DPS / Subtank Difficulty Medium Weapon 2H Axe Contents Overview Skills Gameplay Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS / Subtank Difficulty Medium Strengths High HP pool and invincibility spell (similar to Mercenary's immortality) Weaknesses Has no armor penetration passives, which makes it weaker than most classes Why Play It Barbarian-feel class, thirsty to cut something with an Axe! Skills Single Target Spinning Blow Blasting Rock Cut AoE Shuddering Flame Thunderbolt Wind Cut Whirlwind Assault Energy Bomb Zephyr Strike Toggles / Buffs Steel Presence this is the skill you aim to have in all your gear Spiracle of Vitality Behemoth Force Provocation Essence of Thunder reduces single target enemy attack speed by 30% Essence of Invulnerability you receive 0 damage for a short duration Barbarian Rage Berserker Rage triggers automatically Healing Energy Charge Spiracle Rush Racial Mental Concentration Gaia racial skill Gameplay Weapon choice: 2H Axe for more skill damage. Use Zephyr Strike or Earth Shaker to apply Tactical Advantage, then use your AoE skills. Rotation 1: Earth Shaker + Thunderbolt Wind Cut + Shuddering Flame Rotation 2: Zephyr Strike + Whirlwind Assault + Energy Bomb + Thunderbolt Wind Cut Healing order: Always use Energy Charge first to consume all Spiracles, then use Spiracle Rush . If you use Spiracle Rush while you still have Spiracles, you will not heal anything. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 2 | 1 6 TP 2 | 2 | 2 7 TP 2 | 2 | 3 Stats Priority Stats Damage 100% critical rate, Critical Power (CP), STR → ordered by priority Defense Vitality → more Vitality means more HP Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ STR/20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, P.atk depends on what you need. Pets & Belt Slot Recommendation Belt pets Cheap setup: 2 Kenta, 1 Cube S1, Lunacy card (very important) Normal setup: 3 Mino S3, 2 Unicorns S5 + Lunacy / Devil Skeleton / P.Hector More tankiness: 3 Mino, 2 Unicorn + Yushiva / Devil Skeleton / Lunacy Summoned pet Bloodthirsty Slaughterer or Ethereal Pixie Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with Steel Presence, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal Accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info Accuracy Target RoA 1000+ Accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ Accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ Accuracy Evasion Target RoA / Hroa 3000+ Evasion ⇒ This is an approximate target stats !! Item Stat Examples Accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 2: Title Location Strength Vitality Akt II, Scene IV Allegro Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt II, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt II, Scene IV Andante Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt II, Scene III Allegro Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 Even if this class is not Agility based, Evasion helps tremendously , don't hesitate to try Wind Pixie + Wind Pixie pot if you want more survival. 02 Save your Essence of Invulnerability for boss encounters like the Reviac room. Endgame Performance 5 /10 Solo Ability 6 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Cardinal — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/cardinal/", "text": "Cardinal — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Cardinal C Class Guide Cardinal A Tier Role DPS / Subheal Difficulty Intermediate Weapon 1H Staff + Magewall Contents Overview Skills Gameplay Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS / Subheal Difficulty Intermediate Strengths Many AoEs and Crowd Control skills Weaknesses Low HP, but easily compensated with good positioning and good use of Crowd Control skills Why Play It The game version of a white wizard Skills Passive Vortex Magic your main skill in gear Skills that trigger Vortex Magic Arctic Blast Frost Spear Frozen Snare Cold Bolt Acid Swamp Earthquake Skills to cast after triggering Vortex Magic Rainbow Field Shining Buster Shining Cross Heaven's Spear Mighty Energy Beat Crowd Control Snowslide Divine Nova Utility Magical Requisition Minor Shining Weapon Gameplay The gameplay is very intuitive: cast a trigger spell to proc Vortex Magic on mobs, then follow up with another AoE for amplified damage, boosted further with Magical Requisition . Example rotation: Pull mobs with Mighty Energy Beat → cast Magical Requisition → stack mobs → cast Arctic Blast to proc Vortex Magic → follow up with Rainbow Field for amplified AoE damage. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 3 | 0 6 TP 2 | 3 | 1 7 TP 2 | 3 | 2 Stats Priority Stats Damage Critical Rate, Critical Power (CP), INT → ordered by priority Defense Vitality → more Vitality means more HP and P.Def Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ INT / 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, M.Acc, or M.Atk depending on what you need. Defense Rings with 40+ Vitality / 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, M.Acc, or M.Atk depending on what you need. Pets & Belt Slot Recommendation Belt pets Cheap setup: 3 White Dragons S1 or 3 Ethereal Pixies S2 + Mephisto/Lunacy/M.Hector card Normal setup: 3 Ethereal Pixies S2, 2 unicorns S5, Snowman Summoned pet Ethereal Pixie Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with your main skill, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. You always prioritize stats like the following item: Perfect Staff Example Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal M.accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info M.accuracy Target RoA 1000+ M.accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ M.accuracy DD6 (level 180) 1500+ M.accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ M.accuracy Item Stat Examples M.accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 4: Title Location Intelligence Wisdom Akt IV, Scene IV Presto Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt IV, Scene IV Vivace Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt IV, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt IV, Scene III Presto Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 Kiting is very important with this class , prioritize movement speed in rings. 02 Use Divine Shield for hard encounters to buy time and avoid lethal damage. Endgame Performance 9 /10 Solo Ability 10 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Corruptor — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/corruptor/", "text": "Corruptor — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Corruptor C Class Guide Corruptor D Tier Role DPS Difficulty Hard Weapon 1H Staff + Magewall Contents Overview Skills Rotation Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame ⚠ Just a template for now — will be updated when the classes are rebalanced. Overview Role DPS Difficulty Hard Strengths A lot of control skills, high damage, shines late game Weaknesses Could be hard to master at the beginning Why Play It Cool animations, a lot of AOEs, this is your wizard-like class! Skills Main Skills Active: Spammables: Chain Lightning Inferno Fire Arrow Maelstrom Bolt Fireball Flame Burn AoE Spells: Lightning Field Fire Field Fire Storm AoE Control Spells: Meteor Shower Abyssal Grip Heaven's Breaker Splash Thunder Cooldown Resetter: Dark Spiral Healing Spell: Life Leech Self Buffs: Spirit of Fire Tempest Heed of the Conjuror Grim Attrition Defensive Buffs: Neutralize Magic Magic Skin Passive: Crystal Aura your main skill in gear Timelapse Rotation Single Target: Use spammable spells above AoE: The play style of VM seems complicated at first but it’s actually very easy to understand. We make sure to cast all our self buffs then cast our Fields spells: Lightning Field , Fire Field , Fire Storm and then we hit them with Dark Spiral that will proc Timelapse passive and allows us to cast fields again. So the rotation will look like this: Pull mobs → Fields → AoE Control Skill → Dark Spiral → reset skills → Fields again → AoE Control Skill → Dark Spiral = reset skills. Sometimes you will not reset your fields with Dark Spiral or you cast Fields but Dark Spiral is not ready, in this scenario keep spamming Chain Lightning until your spells are ready to be cast again. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 0 | 3 | 2 6 TP 1 | 3 | 2 7 TP 2 | 3 | 2 Stats Priority Stats Damage 100% critical rate, Critical Power (CP), Int → ordered by priority Defense Agility → more Agility means more HP and Evasion and more mana (stack with CA?) Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ INT / 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, P.atk depends on what you need. Pets & Belt Slot Recommendation Belt pets Cheap setup: 3 White Dragons S1 or 3 Ethereal Pixies S2 + Mephisto/Lunacy/M.Hector card Normal setup: 3 Ethereal Pixies S2, 2 unicorns S5, Snowman Summoned pet Wind Pixie until 230+, then change to Ethereal Pixie Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with your main skill, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. You always prioritize stats like the following item: Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal M.accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info M.accuracy Target RoA 1000+ M.accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ M.accuracy DD6 (level 180) 1500+ M.accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ M.accuracy Item Stat Examples M.accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 4: Title Location Intelligence Wisdom Akt IV, Scene IV Presto Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt IV, Scene IV Vivace Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt IV, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt IV, Scene III Presto Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 Honey water, mana scroll, and mana potions will be very useful early game. 02 Make sure to always use Wind Pixie potion for better survivability. 03 Always use Deep Evasion before pulling, it will reset thanks to Timelapse. 04 Stack INT in all your gear, prioritize INT over m.atk in awakenings. 05 Use Wind Pixie encouragement for a huge boost during boss fights. 06 Some people look for items with evasion but also with perf.block (since we use Mage wall, this stat can help). 07 At SF level, once you become able to solo buffalos, the 1h legendary staff 110 is used instead of your main weapon (same damage and less Freeze and durability problems). Endgame Performance 9 /10 Solo Ability 10 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Deadeye — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/deadeye/", "text": "Deadeye — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Deadeye D Class Guide Deadeye S Tier Role DPS Difficulty Easy Weapon Crossbow Contents Overview Skills Rotation Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS Difficulty Easy Strengths Has huge damage and can spam AoE Weaknesses Weak to magical attacks, easily countered in PvP with Abhuva boss card. Why Play It If you like shooting arrows in all directions every 0.3 seconds, this is the class! Skills Active Piercing Arrow Poison Shot Passive Wild Instinct Burning Style You can aim for both these skills in your gear: WI for more tanking capabilities Burning Style for more damage and less tanking. Recommendation: start with WI gear first and when you reach end game (240+) you can switch to full Burning Style. Useful Skills Cry of Arrows for burst windows Deflecting Aiming for burst windows Cascade of Darkness for an AoE slow Sudden Rush for maximum speeeeeeeeeeed! Demonic Howl Buff skill Veteran Senses Buff skill Rotation The play style of Deadeye is very simple: Thanks to Combat Prowess every time you autoattack you reduce the cooldown of your Piercing Arrow . So you’ll be spamming Auto Attack + Piercing Arrow as your main rotation and whenever Piercing Arrow is not ready, you cast Poison Shot. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 3 | 0 6 TP 2 | 3 | 1 7 TP 2 | 3 | 2 Stats Priority Stats Damage 100% critical rate, Critical Power (CP), DEX → ordered by priority Defense Agility → more Agility means more HP and Evasion Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ AGI/DEX, 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, P.atk depends on what you need. Pets & Belt Belt Pets: Cheap: 2 Kenta, 2 Unicorn S3 Normal: 4 x S5 Forest Pixies + Snowman Summoned Pet: Wind Pixie is your best friend! Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with Wild Instinct, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. You always prioritize stats like the following item: Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal Accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info Accuracy Target RoA 1000+ Accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ Accuracy DD6 (level 180) 1500+ Accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ Accuracy Evasion Target RoA / Hroa 3000+ Evasion DD6 8000+ Evasion ⇒ This is an approximate target stats !! Item Stat Examples Accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Dex/Agility Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 3: Title Location Agility Dexterity Akt III, Scene IV Grave Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt III, Scene IV Adagio Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt III, Scene IV Largo Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt III, Scene III Grave Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 To be continued Endgame Performance 10 /10 Solo Ability 10 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Magus — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/magus/", "text": "Magus — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Magus M Class Guide Magus A Tier Role DPS / Subheal Difficulty Intermediate Weapon 2H Axe Contents Overview Skills Gameplay Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS / Subheal Difficulty Intermediate Strengths Huge AoE DoT damage and powerful single target Weaknesses Low HP pool; high threat skills makes it hard to play within Parties Why Play It Channel the forces of nature as a druid-like caster, wielding earth, fire, and wind to devastate entire groups of enemies Skills Passives Cyclone Lord's Blessing your main skill in gear Mental Link Single Target Explosion of Petrifaction Tectonic Spike Scorching Flame Shackle of the Ground Bleak Squall AoE Spells Eternal Pillar of Fire Root of Mother Nature Vacuum Shockwave Spear of Flame Huge Rock Fall Utility Tears of Gaia free revive while keeping your buffs Enchant Weapon: Water Focused Gust Arcane Swell Recklessness of Earth Recklessness of Thunder Recklessness of Fire Recklessness of Water Gameplay Weapon choice: Cyclone Lord's Blessing converts P.Atk to M.Atk. Combined with Two-Handed Axe Training and Tactical Advantage , a 2H Axe is the obvious weapon choice (this may change at level 220+, to be confirmed). Basic rotation: Pull mobs with Bleak Squall → stack mobs → cast Root of Mother Nature to root them in place → then unleash your AoEs: Eternal Pillar of Fire , Vacuum Shockwave , Spear of Flame . Once your damage is high enough, alternate between Eternal Pillar of Fire and Root of Mother Nature across pulls, both have huge damage modifiers, so using both in the same pull wastes potential. Magus is the only class that benefits enormously from summoning a pet thanks to Mental Link , which lets you inherit INT and Wisdom from your summoned pet. This is why Ethereal Pixie is a must-have and will boost your damage by an insane amount. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 3 | 0 6 TP 2 | 3 | 1 7 TP 2 | 3 | 2 Stats Priority Stats Damage Critical Rate, Critical Power (CP), STR → ordered by priority Defense Vitality → more Vitality means more HP and P.Def Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ STR / 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, M.Acc, or M.Atk depending on what you need. Defense Rings with 40+ Vitality / 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, M.Acc, or M.Atk depending on what you need. Pets & Belt Slot Recommendation Early Setup 2 Kenta + 2 Naga Normal Setup 3 Salamander S5 + M.Hector card Full Setup 3 White Dragons S1 + 2 Kenta + Reviac, Devil Skeleton, Troll Hunter boss cards Summoned Pet Ethereal Pixie Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with your main skill, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal M.accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info M.accuracy Target RoA 1000+ M.accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ M.accuracy DD6 (level 180) 1500+ M.accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ M.accuracy Item Stat Examples M.accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 4: Title Location Intelligence Wisdom Akt IV, Scene IV Presto Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt IV, Scene IV Vivace Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt IV, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt IV, Scene III Presto Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 Kiting is very important with this class — prioritize movement speed in rings. 02 Stage Ethereal Pixie to Stage 5 as soon as possible and equip a Yushiva belt on her — huge boost to your M.Atk. 03 Hector level 2 potion is the best potion to boost your M.Atk. 04 Always keep healing DoT and healing spells ready in case you get hit. 05 If you have trouble stacking mobs, keep circling around them until they are all in one place for Root of Mother Nature. 06 Use all Recklessness skills and Arcane Swell during boss encounters for a significant damage burst. Endgame Performance 9 /10 Solo Ability 9 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Marksman — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/marksman/", "text": "Marksman — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Marksman M Class Guide Marksman D Tier Role DPS Difficulty Easy Weapon Crossbow Contents Overview Skills Rotation Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame ⚠ Just a template for now — will be updated when the classes are rebalanced. Overview Role DPS Difficulty Easy Strengths Has huge damage and can spam AoE Weaknesses Weak to magical attacks, easily countered in PvP with Abhuva boss card. Why Play It If you like shooting arrows in all directions every 0.3 seconds, this is the class! Skills Main Skills Active: Piercing Arrow Poison Shot Passive: Wild Instinct Burning Style You can aim for both these skills in your gear: WI for more tanking capabilities Burning Style for more damage and less tanking. Recommendation: start with WI gear first and when you reach end game (240+) you can switch to full Burning Style. Useful Skills Cry of Arrows and Deflecting Aiming for burst windows Cascade of Darkness for an AoE slow Sudden Rush for maximum speeeeeeeeeeed! Buff skills: Demonic Howl and Veteran Senses Rotation The play style of Deadeye is very simple: Thanks to Combat Prowess every time you autoattack you reduce the cooldown of your Piercing Arrow . So you’ll be spamming Auto Attack + Piercing Arrow as your main rotation and whenever Piercing Arrow is not ready, you cast Poison Shot. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 3 | 0 6 TP 2 | 3 | 1 7 TP 2 | 3 | 2 Stats Priority Stats Damage 100% critical rate, Critical Power (CP), DEX → ordered by priority Defense Agility → more Agility means more HP and Evasion Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ AGI/DEX, 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, P.atk depends on what you need. Pets & Belt Belt Pets: Cheap: 2 Kenta, 2 Unicorn S3 Normal: 4 x S5 Forest Pixies + Snowman Summoned Pet: Wind Pixie is your best friend! Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with Wild Instinct, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. You always prioritize stats like the following item: Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal Accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info Accuracy Target RoA 1000+ Accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ Accuracy DD6 (level 180) 1500+ Accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ Accuracy Evasion Target RoA / Hroa 3000+ Evasion DD6 8000+ Evasion ⇒ This is an approximate target stats !! Item Stat Examples Accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Dex/Agility Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 3: Title Location Agility Dexterity Akt III, Scene IV Grave Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt III, Scene IV Adagio Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt III, Scene IV Largo Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt III, Scene III Grave Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 To be continued Endgame Performance 10 /10 Solo Ability 10 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Master Breeder — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/master-breeder/", "text": "Master Breeder — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Master Breeder M Class Guide Master Breeder A Tier Role DPS / Tank / Heal (thanks to pets) Difficulty Easy Weapon Crossbow / Magewall Contents Overview Skills Rotation Main Skills of Pets Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Leveling Progression Pet Farm Titles Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS / Tank / Heal (thanks to pets) Difficulty Easy Strengths Very strong early game thanks to amazing synergy with Ethereal Pixie and Crystal Golem Weaknesses Once you reach 220 contents, the performance drops significantly Why Play It If you want to experience the summoner theme of the game, this is the class! Skills Active Skills Summon Mastery Allows you to summon 2 pets at the same time Bestial Cry Grim Desire Defense Mastery Trait Mastery Empowering Scent Elemental Resistances Passive Skills Creature Mastery Breeder’s Synergy Expert Caretaker Holy Link Potency This is your main skill in gear! Rotation Potency makes Master Breeder excel with 2 types of pets: Pets that scale with Max Mana Pets that scale with Max HP Which is why the most famous combo for Master Breeder is Ethereal Pixie + Crystal Golem . Ethereal Pixie is your main DPS Crystal Golem is your tank Main Skills of Pets Best Skills to Use on Ethereal Pixie Elemental Harmony Staged toggle skill Blazing Storm AoE spell with DoT Steam Bomb AoE spell Scalding Rain AoE spell Phoenix Impact Triggers Kindling passive that boosts INT/M.Atk Shadow Illusion Dethreat skill Encouragement +200% INT Healing spells: Purifying Flames, Phoenix Embrace, Undine Blessing Important passives: Otherworldly Wisdom, Mysticism (Staged), Kindling Best Skills to Use on Crystal Golem Ruby Eruption High threat AoE Topaz Tantrum AoE stun Diamond Dust AoE Titanite Toggle that increases Threat, HP and Vitality Wonderstone Damage taken removed from Mana Threatening Essence Threat toggle Encouragement +100% STR/VIT Important passives: Rhodochrosite Might, Diamond Skin, Razor Sharp Iolite, Peridot Pain (Staged) Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 0 | 3 6 TP 2 | 1 | 3 7 TP 2 | 2 | 3 Stats Priority Stat Main Stat Critical Power Sub Stat Critical Power (140 CP stones stack with 160 CP stones) Accessories Slot Recommendation Rings 2 × Rings +5 Creature Mastery from Circus / 170 rings (+20 CP) awakened with CP Belt All passives and Magical/Beneficial Deva Pets & Belt Setup Details Early Setup 3 White Dragons S1 + Lion boss card Full Setup 3 White Dragons + 2 Snowman + Reviac + Mephisto + Lion / Butcher Summoned Pets Ethereal Pixie + Crystal Golem Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) 1 Crossbow with 6% P.Atk, 120 STR + Magewall with 6% INT +5 Creature Mastery ring and Bear belt from Circus Parallel World gear (either max slots with trash skill, or Potency gear with trash stats / low slots whatever you can find in the Auction House) Island of Gods 2H Staff for your Ethereal Pixie (1300+ M.Atk, 38+ CP), 2H Mace 6% P.Atk, max HP for Crystal Golem Crit Power Deco set from Altar or Lava Gear Yushiva set for increased stats and more Crit Power Medal with Potency Emblem with Potency Optimization The list above is a high-level overview. For maximum efficiency, follow this upgrade order: S5 Ethereal Pixie S5 Crystal Golem Boots +24 as soon as possible (+25 if you can afford it) Helmet +24 +24 weapon on Ethereal Pixie Necklace with % increased damage vs type Sand Cloak +20 Yushiva Belt on both pets if Stage 5 Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Pet Farm You can level your pets using the Pet Farm . Place your pet in the farm for 12 hours with the basic pass to gain 15% exp , or use the Premium Pass for 60% . A Creature Farm Cracker increases the exp earned by an additional 100% . Titles Aim for titles with INT from Underground Dungeons Stage 4: Title Location Intelligence Wisdom Akt IV, Scene IV Presto Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt IV, Scene IV Vivace Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt IV, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt IV, Scene III Presto Crystal Valley +22 +18 Tips 01 Get a Defense Mastery set to increase the damage reduction on your buff. 02 Awaken all your accessories and Crossbow/Magewall with CP. 03 If you want to farm Rupees in Lake Kaia, it is better to have 2 Wind Pixies S0. 04 Move your pets with Shift + Left Click . 05 Purse of Invocation from the Cash Shop is a huge boost to your pets (500 coins). 06 If your pets are Stage 5, you can put a Yushiva Belt on them to increase all skills by 1 level. Endgame Performance 7 /10 Solo Ability 8 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Mercenary — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/mercenary/", "text": "Mercenary — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Mercenary M Class Guide Mercenary A Tier Role DPS / Tank Difficulty Easy Weapon Spear (2H) Contents Overview Skills Gameplay Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS / Tank Difficulty Easy Strengths Easy survivability in early game Weaknesses Jack of all trades, master of none Why Play It The typical Excalibur class — just with a Spear (which is still cool) Skills Toggles / Buffs Blessing Divine Cluster Holy Aura Defensive Stance Invigorating Essence — your main skill in gear! Single Target Divine Cross Laser Blade AoE Wild Stream Dual Strike Deathblow Utility Hate Aura — for pulling Light Speed — for… speeeeeeeed Immortality — survive at 1 HP for a few seconds Provocation Divine Flash — prevents mobs from attacking for 2 seconds Breakers Offense Breaker Defense Breaker Mental Breaker Passives Lust for Blood — alt skill on gear if no Invigorating Essence Desperate Deflection Frantic Defense Reckless Vivacity Accelerated Casting — requires 2H weapon equipped Gameplay The playstyle of Mercenary is one of if not the easiest in the game, which is why it is always recommended to start with this class as a new player. Activate your buffs and toggles, use Hate Aura to pull mobs, then cast Defense Breaker before your main AoE. This benefits both Tactical Advantage and Lust for Blood in case Holy Aura hasn't procced yet. Then use your main AoE skills: Wild Stream and Dual Strike . Use Divine Flash to prevent mobs from attacking for 2 seconds — a safe window to finish them off. You do not need to worry much about healing and defenses thanks to Desperate Deflection , Frantic Defense , and Reckless Vivacity boosting P.Def, HP, and damage reduction — combined with the Lunacy boss card. You must equip a 2H weapon (preferably Spear 170) to activate Accelerated Casting , which reduces skill cooldowns by 45.5% at level 13 (with R2 Helmet +20, DT buff, and Bear Belt). Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 3 | 2 | 0 6 TP 3 | 3 | 0 7 TP 3 | 3 | 1 9 TP 3 | 3 | 3 Stats Priority Stats Damage Critical Rate, Critical Power, STR Defense Vitality — more Vitality means more HP and P.Def Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ STR / 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, or P.Atk depending on what you need. Defense Rings with 40+ Vitality / 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, or P.Atk depending on what you need. Pets & Belt Setup Details Early 2 Kenta + 1 Cube + Lunacy Normal 3 Mino S1 + Lunacy Full 3 Mino S1 + 2 Snowman + Reviac + Lunacy / P.Hector + Devil Skeleton Belt All passives and Physical Deva Summoned Pet Bloodthirsty Slaughterer Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from Hidden Sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (trash stats 2 slots with Invigorating Aura, or max slots per gear — depends on what you find) Island of Gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization Upgrade the above when applicable (more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 Medusa helmet, better stats on gear). Always prioritize: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal Accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info Accuracy Target RoA 1000+ Accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ Accuracy DD6 (lv 180) 1500+ Accuracy SF (lv 200) 2000+ Accuracy Item Stat Examples Accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Move Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings Exact min/max stats available in the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Reduced Damage Title Camper — Purchase a tent from the Merchant in Hidden Village Underground Dungeons Stage 2 Title Location STR VIT Akt II, Scene IV Allegro Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt II, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt II, Scene IV Andante Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt II, Scene III Allegro Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 Use the Bloodthirsty Slaughterer potion for a significant damage boost. 02 After both AoEs, kite mobs if you're struggling to tank — your mobility is an asset. 03 Save Immortality for critical boss encounters like the Reviac room. 04 Lunacy card is your best friend. Don't leave town without it. 05 You can swap to a shield to activate Deflecting Shield + Shield of Revenge, then switch back to your Spear for hard encounters. Endgame Performance 7 /10 Solo Ability 6 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Oracle — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/oracle/", "text": "Oracle — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Oracle O Class Guide Oracle C Tier Role Healer / Sub DPS Difficulty Easy Weapon 1H Staff + Magewall Contents Overview Skills Gameplay Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame Overview Role Healer / Sub DPS Difficulty Easy Strengths Best healer in the game, unique active toggles (always welcomed in parties) Weaknesses You can solo up to DD6 content, after that you’ll depend on your friend's guild to clear content. Why Play It “Keeping idiots alive” Skills Single Target Mighty Energy Beat AoE Shining Cross Shining Buster Mass Repentance Radiant Flare Heaven's Spear Toggles / Buffs Minor Shining Weapon Hymn of Focus Mass Bless Armor Mass Bless Magic Armor Mass Bless Weapon Mass Bless Magic Power Mass HP Regeneration Mass MP Regeneration Brilliant Harmony (increases Int and M.atk but decreases Crit Power: this is why Oracles can't become DPS) main skill on gear if you are a healer main Divine Shield (almost 100% damage reduction) Guardian Angel (free revive) Gameplay Very simple class, no big brain moves. Opener: Radiant Flare Use Mass Repentance and Shining Cross, they have very low CD. Shining Buster is an insane burst, save it for bosses. Use Divine Shield during boss encounters! Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 3 | 0 or 3 | 2 | 0 (if you want to be a main healer) 6 TP 2 | 3 | 1 7 TP 2 | 3 | 2 Stats Priority Stats Damage 100% critical rate, Critical Power (CP), Int → ordered by priority Defense Vitality → more Vitality means more HP Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ INT / 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, P.atk depends on what you need. Pets & Belt Slot Recommendation Belt pets Cheap setup: 3 White Dragons S1 or 3 Ethereal Pixies S2 + Mephisto/Lunacy/M.Hector card Normal setup: 3 Ethereal Pixies S2, 2 Unicorns S5, Snowman Summoned pet Ethereal Pixie Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with your main skill, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal M.accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info M.accuracy Target RoA 1000+ M.accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ M.accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ M.accuracy Item Stat Examples M.accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 4: Title Location Intelligence Wisdom Akt IV, Scene IV Presto Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt IV, Scene IV Vivace Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt IV, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt IV, Scene III Presto Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 Use Light Saver to remove your threat by 100% 02 Heal! Endgame Performance 5 /10 Solo Ability 6 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Overlord — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/overlord/", "text": "Overlord — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Overlord O Class Guide Overlord A Tier Role DPS / Tank / Heal (thanks to pets) Difficulty Easy Weapon Crossbow / Magewall Contents Overview Skills Rotation Famous Combo Pets Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Leveling Progression Pet Farm Titles Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS / Tank / Heal (thanks to pets) Difficulty Easy Strengths Very strong early game thanks to amazing synergy with Wind Pixie Weaknesses Once you reach 220 contents, the performance drops significantly Why Play It If you want to experience the summoner theme of the game, this is the class Skills Active Skills Summon Mastery Allows you to summon 2 pets at the same time Miraculous Healing Fervor Aura Aura of Inspiration Order of Alacrity Lion’s Claw Passive Skills Creature Mastery Unholy Synergy Blood Synergy This is your main skill in gear! Rotation The playstyle of Overlord is adaptable based on what pet you have, but the general rule is: activate all your toggles / auras, pull mobs, then use an AoE skill. Famous Combo Pets 2 Wind Pixies Alternate Pixie Nova between pulls/rooms. ⚠ Important: Pixie Nova does not stack! In some scenarios you’ll need another pet for short burst (e.g. Crystal Spider, Ethereal Pixie, or Hector). Best Skills to Use on Wind Pixie See the full skill details on the Wind Pixie page. Skills with P.Atk modifiers benefit most from the Blood Synergy build (STR ⇒ P.Atk of Pets). Flare Single target damage skill Pixie Nova Main AoE skill Prominence Burst 1 point is enough; aggro skill usable only if you lost aggro Pixie Glitter Single target healing spell Shadow Illusion Use on 2nd pet only. This dethreat skill lets your 2nd Pixie be a glass cannon while the main Pixie (with this skill disabled) tanks Encouragement Buffs AGI/INT +100%; amazing for boosting tanking capabilities of Wind Pixie Important Passives (Wind Pixie) All passive skills matter: Foresight , Knowledge is Power , Fighter Unit , Celestial Grace (Staged skill), Brilliance , etc. To determine which skills are better, check the Wind Pixie page and look for skills with P.Atk modifiers, since Overlord scales STR ⇒ P.Atk of Pets when using the Blood Synergy build. Alternative Playstyle You can also play Mastermind + Electric Synergy , which works well with Ethereal Pixie and Grandmaster Hector - but this is not recommended for new players. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 3 | 0 | 2 6 TP 3 | 1 | 2 7 TP 3 | 2 | 2 Stats Priority Stat Main Stat STR Sub Stat INT Accessories Slot Recommendation Rings 2 × Rings with +5 Creature Mastery from Circus Belt All passives and Magical/Beneficial Asura Pets & Belt Setup Details Early Setup 2 Kenta, 1 Naga + Magma Golem boss card Full Setup S1 Ogre, S1 Bloodthirsty, S1 Baphomet + 2 Snowman + Magma Golem + Stone Gargoyle + Devil Slaughter Summoned Pets 2 × Wind Pixie Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) 1 Crossbow with 6% P.Atk, 120 STR + Magewall with 6% INT +5 Creature Mastery ring and Bear belt from Circus Parallel World gear (either max slots with trash skill, or Blood Synergy gear with trash stats / low slots whatever you can find in the Auction House) Island of Gods 2-handed Maces for your Wind Pixie with 6% P.Atk, 120 STR, 38+ Critical Power Yushiva set for increased STR/INT stats Medal with Blood Synergy Emblem with Blood Synergy Optimization The list above is a high-level overview. For maximum efficiency, follow this upgrade order: 2x Stage 5 Wind Pixies Boots +24 as soon as possible (+25 if you can afford it) Helmet +24 Pet weapon +24 2x Sand Cloak +20 Gear on Wind Pixies Slot Item Weapon 2H Mace 6% P.Atk, 38 Critical Power Armor (Main Tank) Summoner Reviac Armor ⇒ replace with Sand Cloak +20 Shield Block Shield with 4% P.Atk Belt Yushiva Belt Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Pet Farm You can level your pets using the Pet Farm . Place your pet in the farm for 12 hours with the basic pass to gain 15% exp , or use the Premium Pass for 60% . A Creature Farm Cracker increases the exp earned by an additional 100% . Titles Aim for titles with STR from Underground Dungeons Stage 2: Title Location Strength Vitality Akt II, Scene IV Allegro Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt II, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt II, Scene IV Andante Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt II, Scene III Allegro Crystal Valley +22 +18 Tips 01 To have an easier life as Overlord, make a Master Breeder level 153 for the Defense Mastery buff and a Gnoll Buff which you use on your main tank - this is a game changer! 02 Awaken all your accessories and Crossbow/Magewall with STR. 03 Use Miraculous Healing whenever it’s ready. 04 Move your Wind Pixies with Shift + Left Click after casting Pixie Nova (you can avoid tanking mobs this way if you have a difficult time tanking). 05 Purse of Invocation from the Cash Shop is a huge boost to your pets (500 coins). 06 If your pets are Stage 5, you can put a Yushiva Belt on them. Endgame Performance 7 /10 Solo Ability 7 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Slayer — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/slayer/", "text": "Slayer — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Slayer S Class Guide Slayer S Tier Role DPS / subtank Difficulty Easy Weapon Dual 1H Swords Contents Overview Skills Rotations Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS / subtank Difficulty Easy Strengths Has burst damage and amazing sustain Weaknesses Only 3 main damage skills with ~30sec CD (can go lower with helmet+24 and + cards) Why Play It If you like cool sword animations, easy to progress melee character, this is the class! Skills Main Skills Phantasm Hellstorm Deadly Dancing Apocalypse Phase Blades this is the skill you aim to have in all your gear Useful Skills Gloom Aura for pulling Binding Dust for more dodging and tanking capabilities Smoke Bomb for more dodging and tanking capabilities Sudden Rush for maximum speeeeeeeeeeed! Defensive Buffs Pact with Darkness Shadowforged Plating Cloak of Shadows Distortion Rotations Single Target Phantasm annihilates bosses. AoE / Multi-Target Hellstorm, Deadly Dancing, Apocalypse. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 2 | 1 6 TP 2 | 2 | 2 7 TP 2 | 2 | 3 Stats Priority Stats Damage 100% critical rate, Critical Power (CP), STR → ordered by priority Defense Agility → more Agility means more HP and Evasion Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ STR/20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, P.atk depends on what you need. Pets & Belt Slot Recommendation Belt pets Cheap setup: 2 unicorn S3, 2 kenta s0, Snowman → worth sacrificing 1 unicorn for P.hector card Normal setup: 3 Mino S3, 2 unicorns S5, Snowman Expensive setup: 3 x Death Gladiators S0, 2 snowman/2 cubes/2 S3 picks (depends on what you need) Summoned pet Bloodthirsty Slaughterer or Wind Pixie (depends on the content) Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with Phase blades, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. You always prioritize stats like the following item: Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal Accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info Accuracy Target RoA 1000+ Accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ Accuracy DD6 (level 180) 1500+ Accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ Accuracy Evasion Target RoA / Hroa 3000+ Evasion DD6 8000+ Evasion ⇒ This is an approximate target stats !! Item Stat Examples Accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 2: Title Location Strength Vitality Akt II, Scene IV Allegro Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt II, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt II, Scene IV Andante Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt II, Scene III Allegro Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 You can always switch your Bloodthirsty Slaughterer with a Wind Pixie if you find issues tanking. 02 Lvl 2 potion of the above mentioned pets is a huge boost. 03 When you rotate through rooms in DD6 for example, use Deadly Dancing in a room then Apocalypse + Hellstorm in the other room. Don't use all AOEs in 1 room or you'll end up losing so much time in the next one (this is of course if you can afford killing mobs with 1 or 2 skills only). 04 If you ever pulled mobs by mistake don't run, you have Cloak of Shadows and Distortion! 05 Use Gloom Aura to pull 1 room, then Smoke Bomb to pull the next one. 06 To be continued Endgame Performance 9 /10 Solo Ability 10 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Templar — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/templar/", "text": "Templar — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Templar T Class Guide Templar B Tier Role DPS / subtank Difficulty Easy Weapon 1H Mace + Shield Contents Overview Skills Rotations Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS / subtank Difficulty Easy Strengths Has burst damage and amazing sustain Weaknesses Only 3 main damage skills with ~30sec CD (can go lower with helmet+24 and + cards) Why Play It If you like cool sword animations, easy to progress melee character, this is the class! Skills Main Skills Phantasm Hellstorm Deadly Dancing Apocalypse Phase Blades (this is the skill you aim to have in all your gear) Useful Skills Gloom Aura for pulling Binding Dust and Smoke Bomb for more dodging and tanking capabilities Sudden Rush for maximum speeeeeeeeeeed! Defensive Buffs Pact with Darkness Shadowforged Plating Cloak of Shadows Distortion Rotations Single Target Phantasm annihilates bosses. AoE / Multi-Target Hellstorm, Deadly Dancing, Apocalypse. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 2 | 1 6 TP 2 | 2 | 2 7 TP 2 | 2 | 3 Stats Priority Stats Damage 100% critical rate, Critical Power (CP), STR → ordered by priority Defense Agility → more Agility means more HP and Evasion Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ STR/20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, P.atk depends on what you need. Pets & Belt Slot Recommendation Belt pets Cheap setup: 2 unicorn S3, 2 kenta s0, Snowman → worth sacrificing 1 unicorn for P.hector card Normal setup: 3 Mino S3, 2 unicorns S5, Snowman Expensive setup: 3 x Death Gladiators S0, 2 snowman/2 cubes/2 S3 picks (depends on what you need) Summoned pet Bloodthirsty Slaughterer or Wind Pixie (depends on the content) Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with Phase blades, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. You always prioritize stats like the following item: Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal Accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info Accuracy Target RoA 1000+ Accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ Accuracy DD6 (level 180) 1500+ Accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ Accuracy Evasion Target RoA / Hroa 3000+ Evasion DD6 8000+ Evasion ⇒ This is an approximate target stats !! Item Stat Examples Accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 2: Title Location Strength Vitality Akt II, Scene IV Allegro Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt II, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt II, Scene IV Andante Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt II, Scene III Allegro Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 You can always switch your Bloodthirsty Slaughterer with a Wind Pixie if you find issues tanking. 02 Lvl 2 potion of the above mentioned pets is a huge boost. 03 When you rotate through rooms in DD6 for example, use Deadly Dancing in a room then Apocalypse + Hellstorm in the other room. Don't use all AOEs in 1 room or you'll end up losing so much time in the next one (this is of course if you can afford killing mobs with 1 or 2 skills only). 04 If you ever pulled mobs by mistake don't run, you have Cloak of Shadows and Distortion! 05 Use Gloom Aura to pull 1 room, then Smoke Bomb to pull the next one. 06 To be continued Endgame Performance 9 /10 Solo Ability 10 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "Void Mage — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/void-mage/", "text": "Void Mage — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › Void Mage V Class Guide Void Mage S Tier Role DPS Difficulty Hard Weapon 1H Staff + Magewall Contents Overview Skills Rotation Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS Difficulty Hard Strengths A lot of control skills, high damage, shines late game Weaknesses Could be hard to master at the beginning Why Play It Cool animations, a lot of AOEs, this is your wizard-like class! Skills Spammables Chain Lightning Inferno Fire Arrow Maelstrom Bolt Fireball Flame Burn AoE Spells Lightning Field Fire Field Fire Storm AoE Control Spells Meteor Shower Abyssal Grip Heaven's Breaker Splash Thunder Cooldown Resetter Dark Spiral Healing Spell Life Leech Self Buffs Spirit of Fire Tempest Heed of the Conjuror Grim Attrition Defensive Buffs Neutralize Magic Magic Skin Passive Crystal Aura your main skill in gear Timelapse Rotation Single Target: Use spammable spells above AoE: The play style of VM seems complicated at first but it’s actually very easy to understand. We make sure to cast all our self buffs then cast our Fields spells: Lightning Field , Fire Field , Fire Storm and then we hit them with Dark Spiral that will proc Timelapse passive and allows us to cast fields again. So the rotation will look like this: Pull mobs → Fields → AoE Control Skill → Dark Spiral → reset skills → Fields again → AoE Control Skill → Dark Spiral = reset skills. Sometimes you will not reset your fields with Dark Spiral or you cast Fields but Dark Spiral is not ready, in this scenario keep spamming Chain Lightning until your spells are ready to be cast again. Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 0 | 3 | 2 6 TP 1 | 3 | 2 7 TP 2 | 3 | 2 Stats Priority Stats Damage 100% critical rate, Critical Power (CP), Int → ordered by priority Defense Agility → more Agility means more HP and Evasion and more mana (stack with CA?) Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ INT / 20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, P.atk depends on what you need. Pets & Belt Slot Recommendation Belt pets Cheap setup: 3 White Dragons S1 or 3 Ethereal Pixies S2 + Mephisto/Lunacy/M.Hector card Normal setup: 3 Ethereal Pixies S2, 2 unicorns S5, Snowman Summoned pet Wind Pixie until 230+, then change to Ethereal Pixie Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with your main skill, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. You always prioritize stats like the following item: Perfect Gear Example Perfect Staff Example Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal M.accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info M.accuracy Target RoA 1000+ M.accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ M.accuracy DD6 (level 180) 1500+ M.accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ M.accuracy Item Stat Examples M.accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 4: Title Location Intelligence Wisdom Akt IV, Scene IV Presto Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt IV, Scene IV Vivace Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt IV, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt IV, Scene III Presto Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 Honey water, mana scroll, and mana potions will be very useful early game. 02 Make sure to always use Wind Pixie potion for better survivability. 03 Always use Deep Evasion before pulling, it will reset thanks to Timelapse. 04 Stack INT in all your gear, prioritize INT over m.atk in awakenings. 05 Use Wind Pixie encouragement for a huge boost during boss fights. 06 Some people look for items with evasion but also with perf.block (since we use Mage wall, this stat can help). 07 At SF level, once you become able to solo buffalos, the 1h legendary staff 110 is used instead of your main weapon (same damage and less Freeze and durability problems). Endgame Performance 9 /10 Solo Ability 10 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "War Kahuna — Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Class", "url": "class/war-kahuna/", "text": "War Kahuna — Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home Home › Classes › War Kahuna W Class Guide War Kahuna B Tier Role DPS Difficulty Medium Weapon 2H Axe Contents Overview Skills Note Gameplay Talent Build Stats Accessories Pets & Belt Gear Boss Cards Titles Leveling Progression Tips Endgame Overview Role DPS Difficulty Medium Strengths High burst damage and strong buffs Weaknesses Requires many preparations to make it work; locked from using some items because the class is a Mage but plays like a Warrior; Long CDs Why Play It This is the Shaman class in Rappelz , use all elements to do devastating blows Skills Single Target Spinning Blow Blasting Rock Cut Thunderstorm Slayer AoE Shuddering Flame Huge Volcanic Eruption Rain of Spirit Huge Rock Fall Low DPS but used to apply Tactical Advantage Passives Thicket Armor Mob of Magic Symbiosis BUGGED Breath of Life BUGGED Utility Focused Gust Arcane Swell Recklessness of Earth Recklessness of Thunder Recklessness of Fire Recklessness of Water Impaling Power Gravity Amplification Reduces attack speed of mobs by 60% or more Enchant Weapon: Fire Mental Concentration Gaia racial skill Note Wait, where is the main skill? No important skill is worth the investment into gear for now, which is why everyone is waiting for a rebalance of this class. But if you had to pick one, Recklessness of Earth is recommended , it makes the buff reduce more damage taken and last longer, improving survivability, which is exactly what this class lacks. Gameplay Weapon choice: 2H Axe. Rotation 1: Cast all Recklessness skills + Impaling Power + Focused Gust , then cast Gravity Amplification on mobs, then Shuddering Flames . Rotation 2: Cast Huge Rock Fall , then Huge Volcanic Eruption + Rain of Spirit . Talent Build Points Allocation 5 TP 2 | 3 | 0 6 TP 2 | 3 | 1 7 TP 2 | 3 | 2 Stats Priority Stats Damage 100% critical rate, Critical Power (CP), STR → ordered by priority Defense Vitality → more Vitality means more HP Accessories Setup Accessories Damage Rings with 40+ STR/20+ CP, the 3rd stat could be movement speed, Evasion, P.atk depends on what you need. Pets & Belt Slot Recommendation Belt pets Cheap setup: 2 Kenta, 1 White Dragon S1, P.Hector Normal setup: 3 Mino S1, 2 Naga S0 + Reviac / Devil Skeleton / P.Hector More tankiness: 3 Mino, 2 Unicorn + Yushiva / Devil Skeleton / P.Hector Summoned pet Bloodthirsty Slaughterer or Ethereal Pixie Gear Progression Path R2 helmet +20 (all skills +1) R6 +15 gear from hidden sanctuary Circus weapons and accessories from Circus dungeon Parallel World gear (either trash stats 2 slots with recklessness of earth, or max slots in each gear but trash skill, depends on what you could find) Island of gods weapons and rings DD Accessories and Yushiva belt Lava gear (boots, gloves, armor, helmet) Medal Emblem Optimization You upgrade the above when it's applicable e.g., more slots in belt, +24 weapon, +24 medusa helmet, better stats on gear. Example of purple stats you look for: Evasion and movement speed on boots | Evasion or CP on armor, Emblem, Medal Accuracy on gloves, medal or emblem Stat Targets & Item Stat Info Accuracy Target RoA 1000+ Accuracy Hidden RoA 1200+ Accuracy SF (level 200) 2000+ Accuracy Evasion Target RoA / Hroa 3000+ Evasion ⇒ This is an approximate target stats !! Item Stat Examples Accuracy ~200+ on gloves, emblem, or medal Crit power ~11+ on gloves, emblem, medal Evasion ~160+ on boots, armor, medal, or emblem Movement Speed ~17+ on boots, 30+ on rings You can find the exact min/max stats on the Discord channel (to be imported here soon). Boss Cards Boss cards provide massive stat boosts that rival high-level gear upgrades. Check the full guide for priority cards and collection details: Boss Card Collection Guide → Titles Title for Reduced Damage: Camper (Purchase a tent from Merchant in Hidden Village) Titles from Underground Dungeons Stage 2: Title Location Strength Vitality Akt II, Scene IV Allegro Palmir Plateau +28 +23 Akt II, Scene IV Moderato Palmir Plateau +23 +19 Akt II, Scene IV Andante Palmir Plateau +19 +16 Akt II, Scene III Allegro Crystal Valley +22 +18 Leveling Progression Starting with Rappelz Master Class and Beyond 175 and Beyond Tips 01 Even if this class is not Agility based, Evasion helps tremendously, don't hesitate to try Wind Pixie + Wind Pixie pot if you want more survival. 02 You can sacrifice M.Atk on belt for more Evasion on belt; it works wonders. 03 +10 cards on Recklessness with a +25 helmet makes Recklessness available 24/7, which means you can no longer die with additional buffs like Gnoll Buff, Camper, Deva Blessing Lv2, Obidikar Card and Arcane Guardian , the class becomes A-tier (though it still suffers from Long CDs). Endgame Performance 6 /10 Solo Ability 6 /10 Rappelz Guidelines Fan-made community guide — not affiliated with Valofe"}, {"title": "175 and beyond - RAPPELZ GUIDELINES", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/175-and-beyond/", "text": "175 and beyond - RAPPELZ GUIDELINES RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home 175 and Beyond Level 175 - 180: Devildom (DD) Devildom is the primary farming dungeon for this level range. Enter via the Kaia chain quest. Difficulty Experience Notes DD2 1 hour SS = 20% exp You should be able to solo this easily with previous setup. DD3 Much faster exp Possible for most classes - easier for some than others. Class-dependent difficulty. DD4 Highest difficulty Completely different scale. Don't get demotivated if you can't clear yet. Key Drops: Crystals for gear upgrades and DD accessories (8 types that you must collect same as you did for Circus Accessories: Spirit, Undead, Mecca, Beasts, Ains, Dragons, Devils, Antique) Priority: Daily DD runs | Rupee farming | Acquire PW gear for your main class | Upgrade skill cards to +6/+7 Gear Target: At this phase you should be focusing on your dailies DD1/2/3, farming Rupees, finding better PW gear with your main class skill, and getting your skill cards +6/+7. Once you do all of this, farm Rupees to buy Lava gear set (sometimes sold for 25B per piece - Head, Armor, Gloves, Boots) which is a universal upgrade usable for your future classes and can boost your damage by an insane amount. - Lava weapon can be sold for 35B to 50B. Buy buffs for 5B from Players => I can't stress enough how important this is. Once you test it you will be addicted to these buffs forever. Target Gear for Level 175-180 Equipment Specifications Belt Yushiva 8-slot (Antique stone) Weapon +20 (1/32), upgrade to +25 (32/32) over time Defense P.def not important past ~75k. Focus on Evasion: 8k+ (DE/Slayer), 4k+ (others) Helmet +22 minimum with +2 all skills Boss Cards Devil Skeleton (+30% damage type) | Reviac (+100 CP, -100% Crit) | P.Hector / M.Hector Level 180 - 190 If you're able to solo DD4/DD5 after following the previous steps and meeting the target gear requirements, then you can level yourself all the way to 195 in less than 2 weeks. Your goal would be the following: - Crafting Sand Cloak (equipable lvl 190) - Crafting Reviac Gear => crafting guide is in official Discord If you leveled yourself then you will already have 50% of the needed materials to craft the gear. Always upgrade armor first:. Upgrade Path Priority Notes Boots, Gloves, Helmet Keep Current Maintain Nusy gear for these slots Armor TOP PRIORITY Upgrade path: Nusy > Flumi > Inferno > Reviac Reviac Helmet 2nd Priority Provides +10% evasion bonus Remaining Gear 3rd Priority Complete Reviac set after armor and helmet Target Gear for Level 180-190 Equipment Specifications Cloak Sand Cloak +20 (upgrade with Dark Cubes) Armor Full Reviac Gear with main class skill +1 Belt Yushiva Antique 8-slot (+22 minimum) Weapon +24 or higher Helmet +24 minimum Decorative gear Full Lava Set ( without cloak & Mask since they are expensive and you can aim to craft them yourself once you hit 200+ by doing Vulcano dailies Rings +20 CP from Island of Gods, Awakened with CP Accessories Full DD Accessories (all 8 types), Awakened with CP Cards Devil Skeleton, Reviac Card, Hector/Lunacy Level 190 - 220 If you don't have the gear listed above, you won't be able to do much in SF. Farming all of this will allow you to solo DD6 and level yourself all the way to 200+. Target Gear for Level 190-210 Equipment Specifications Accessories Sky Set (accessories + Chaos Stone), enhanced with your main stat. Stop at +6 or +7. Helmet Luciad Iron Mask with +20 CP Craftables Cloak, Advanced Wings, Mask - all gained from Vulcanos 210 x10 daily runs Progression Note: veteran players choose to join a powerlevel from 190 to 220 because it is the fastest and most efficient way to gain a boost in stats, more access to TPs, and unlocking Maze/SF and TU dailies ASAP. The other alternative is to join a guild and do SF runs together until you hit 220. . RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Beyond Master Class", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/beyond-master-class/", "text": "Beyond Master Class RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Beyond Master Class Level progression from 153 to 175 with optimized gear and farming strategies. Level 153–160: Early Endgame Choose one of the following methods based on your class strength and gear: Method Location Difficulty Description Method 1 UG Quests Easy Take from village teleport NPCs. Pop Stamina Saver and Growth potions. Spam UG 2 Palmir until level 160. Method 2 Snow Basin Medium Kill dragons until level 160. Best for Void Mage or Berserker (AoE abilities make it easier to kite). Method 3 Labyrinth Dungeon Medium Do quests to final boss summoning Butkada and Akshas. Take quest → kill boss → abandon. +5% exp per run. Method 4 Island of Gods Hard & Fast Buy Boarding Pass from Black Marketer. 30-min solo to level 160. Not recommended for new players - alts only. Level 160–175: Gear Progression Checklist Step Item / Set Details 1 PW Gear Set From the farming above you are surely able to buy PW set from Auction House. The set is called: - Daman - For Hunters - Mach - For Warriors - Nemon - For Mages - Skadi - For Summoners. Buy Boots, Armor, Gloves - prefer 3-slot, cheapest possible. 2 Pets & Belt Death Tyrant 150 (+1 skill) | Bear Belt with passives + Gaia/Asura/Deva skills. 3 Helmet & Awakening Make Helmet R2+20 from Moonlight Dungeon. Awaken with Awakening Stones (Black Marketer Nostra Family). 4 Unity & Potion Wind Pixie / Ethereal Pixie / Bloodthirster (class-dependent). Spam use as level 1 potion every hour. Best Leveling Location: Remains of Ancients (RoA) To enter: Complete a quest at Circus 3 (starts at City of Ruins Hector NPC). If you followed the previous steps, RoA will be easy for you. Farm here for an hour or more - this step defines your future leveling speed for years to come. Circus Drops (Game Changers) Circus 3 drops Necklace + Earrings with bonus damage and damage reduction to mobs. Highest priority types: Undead, Beast, and Mecca. You'll need 2 earrings + 1 necklace of the same type to switch depending on the mobs you face in RoA. Pro tip: If your class can handle Circus 4, go for it - the drops are much better. Target Gear for RoA Farming Equipment Specifications Weapon +12 Circus with Accuracy stat (Mystic Jewel +500 ATK from Alvaria). Awakened with Weapon Stones. Accessories Earrings + Necklace (multiple types). Awakened with Accessory Stones. Rings Circus Rings with effects (+ATK or +stats) Belt Bear Belt +1 (4-slot). Easy to make with Belt Upgrader Kit drops. Armor PW gear +7 Pets 3 Pets + Boss Card setup. New pet level 150. Cards Lunacy or Mephisto Card Farming Island of Gods for weapons/accessories 170+, or buy from AH ✓ With this setup: Solo RoA even in Hector Room and level to 175. With a friend having the same gear, you can do HRoA First Room. What’s Next? Ready to continue your journey beyond level 175? Check out the 175 and beyond guide for the complete progression roadmap. RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Boss Card Collection", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/boss-card-collection/", "text": "Boss Card Collection RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Boss Card Collection This is something new players ignore while it has as high impact as a weapon +20 or even more. Easy to get boss cards from Flea. Cheap and high priority boss cards for a quick boost Boss Card Qty Bonuses Obsidicar x7 +200 M.ATK MicroRaptor x5 +150 P.ATK , +150 M.ATK Mephisto x5 +10 Crit Power , +2% Crit Rate Lilith x5 +200 P.ATK , +200 M.ATK Ent x3 +150 P.ATK Yushiva x3 +5000 HP , +5000 MP Devil Slaughter x3 +200 P.ATK , +200 M.ATK Stone Gargoyle x3 +200 P.ATK , +200 M.ATK Devil Reviac x3 +30 Crit Power , +300 P.ATK , +300 M.ATK Dark Alchemist Saragon x3 +10% Crit Rate , +450 P.ATK , +450 M.ATK Bloodthirsty Beast Karmos x3 +50 VIT , +2000 Max HP Shadow of Reaper Necro x3 +50 STR , +50 INT Final Combined Stats Stat Value Physical Attack +1650 P.ATK Magic Attack +1700 M.ATK Critical Rate +12% Critical Power +40 Max HP +7000 Max MP +5000 Vitality +50 VIT Strength +50 STR Intelligence +50 INT 💰 Cost Estimate: 5-7 billion rupees A huge free boost compared to other upgrades. Feel free to check the Boss card discord channel for more bonuses that are not mentioned here. Complete Boss Card Collection Below is the full list of all 61 boss cards organized by rarity. Collecting all cards requires 358 cards total . Normal (x10 Cards — 14 Boss Cards = 140 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Baron Madius P Atk +30 Emmanuel Raymond Cast Spd +2 Ultimate Witch M Def +30 Bear Mother Critical Rate +2 Oforia P Def +30 Abhuva Evasion +5 Primal Scream M Atk +50 Taranida P Atk +50 Crustalino Atk Spd +3 Likirus M Atk +80 Soulseeker P Acc +5 Takin Max Weight +100 Lucius M Acc +5 Silex the Giant Max HP +150 Rare (x7 Cards — 13 Boss Cards = 91 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Kiscia the Beautiful P Atk +80 , P Acc +5 Lady Ruina P Acc +10 Aurumis P Atk +100 Dominatus the Mad M Atk +80 , M Acc +5 Queen Eratia M Def +100 Ilrios Max HP +200 , Max Weight +200 Betrayal Max HP +200 , Max MP +100 Ashmaw the Devourer M Atk +100 , Cast Spd +3 Sand Lord Kynish P Def +100 Draka Atk Spd +3 , Max HP +100 Queen Eva Evasion +10 , P Acc +5 Obsidicar M Atk +200 Vulcanus Creature Taming +1 Lvl Special (x5 Cards — 15 Boss Cards = 75 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Butkadah M Def +150 , M Acc +5 Medusa Block Def +200 , P Def +150 Black Widow P Def +150 , M Def +150 Microraptor P Atk +150 , M Atk +150 Bone Dragon M Def +150 , Max MP +300 Mephisto Critical Rate +2 , Critical Power +10 Lilith P Atk +200 , M Atk +200 Soul of Lunacy P Def +150 , Max HP +500 Ent P Atk +150 , Atk Spd +2 Cruel Tula HP Recovery +200 , MP Recovery +200 Lion Max HP +100 , Max MP +100 Barga Evasion +15 , M Res +15 Kraken P Def +150 , Max HP +50 Red Eye Troll Hunter Max HP +2,500 , P Def +1,000 Cruel Troll Hunter Critical Power +10 , P Atk +250 , M Atk +250 Unique (x3 Cards — 14 Boss Cards = 42 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Courage of Grand Master Hector P Atk +500 , Max HP +500 , P Acc +15 Knowledge of Grand Master Hector M Atk +500 , Max MP +300 , M Acc +15 Crystal Golem P Def +500 , M Def +200 , Max HP +1,500 Bloodthirsty Slaughterer M Def +500 , P Def +200 , Max MP +1,000 Yushiva Max HP +5,000 , Max MP +3,000 , Max Weight +500 Wooden Devil P Pierce +150 , M Pierce +150 Devil Slaughterer P Atk +200 , M Atk +200 Stone Gargoyle P Atk +200 , M Atk +200 Magma Golem Max HP +300 , Max MP +300 Crazy Hagen Block Def +300 , P Def +100 , M Def +100 Devil Reviac Critical Power +30 , P Atk +300 , M Atk +300 Devil Skeleton Crit Pow +20 , P Atk +350 , M Atk +350 , Crit Rate +5 Dark Alchemist Saragon Crit Rate +10 , P Atk +450 , M Atk +450 Bloodthirsty Beast Karmos VIT +50 , P Def +2,000 Epic (x2 Cards — 5 Boss Cards = 10 Cards) Boss Card Bonuses Chaotic Phoenix: Warrior P Atk +5% Chaotic Phoenix: Magician M Atk +5% Chaotic Phoenix: Summoner STR +30 , VIT +30 , INT +30 , Crit Pow +20 Shadow of Reaper, Necron STR +50 , INT +50 Butcher Vulcan Critical Power +30 , P Pierce +500 , M Pierce +500 Max Achievable Stats (All 61 Cards Collected) Stat Value STR 80 INT 80 VIT 80 Physical Attack 3,010 + 5% Magical Attack 3,220 + 5% Physical Defense 4,530 Magical Defense 1,380 Physical Accuracy 40 Magical Accuracy 30 Attack Speed 8 Cast Speed 5 Max HP 11,100 Max MP 5,100 HP Recovery 200 MP Recovery 200 Critical Rate 19 Critical Power 90 Evasion 30 M Res 15 P Pierce 650 M Pierce 650 Block Defense 500 Max Weight 800 Creature Taming +1 Lvl Total Cards Needed: Normal = 14 Boss Cards (140 cards) | Rare = 13 Boss Cards (91 cards) | Special = 15 Boss Cards (75 cards) Unique = 14 Boss Cards (42 cards) | Epic = 5 Boss Cards (10 cards) Grand Total = 61 Boss Cards — 358 Cards for Collection RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Enhanced Teardrops Upgrade Guide (+5 / +10)", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/how-to-make-teardrops-5-10/", "text": "Enhanced Teardrops Upgrade Guide (+5 / +10) ← Back to Home Enhanced Teardrops (+5 / +10) Enhanced Teardrops can be leveled up to +10 via the Soul Crafter NPC . +1 to +5 — Soul Stone Essence Soul Stone Essence — dropped in the Maze Dungeon . Use Soul Stone Essence to upgrade your Enhanced Teardrops from +1 up to +5 . +5 to +10 — Volatile Soul Stone Essence Volatile Soul Stone Essence — available from the Cash Shop . Use Volatile Soul Stone Essence to upgrade from +5 to +10 . Volatile Soul Stone Essence can technically be used from +1 to +10 , but it is a Cash Shop item. Save it for the +5 → +10 range where the free alternative is not available. Recommendation Use Soul Stone Essence (Maze Dungeon drop) from +1 to +5 Use Volatile Soul Stone Essence (Cash Shop) from +5 to +10"}, {"title": "General Tips and Tricks", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/general-tips/", "text": "General Tips and Tricks RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home General Tips & Tricks Essential advice for efficient leveling, gear progression, and gameplay optimization. Strategic Leveling Tips Tip Key Point Survivability over Damage Most players rush for damage but then complain about dying. Prioritize survivability while gearing up at low levels. A Soul of Lunacy card is one of the cheapest and best choices for most classes without healing skills. Vulc Questline Timing Start the daily Vulc questline early as soon as you hit 175 (the quest gives free +1 upgrade cube with 100% chance but it makes the gear bound so use it on food only). Keep R2+20 Helmet Hold onto your R2+20 helmet and keep gear in Distorted (160) until you can afford a +20 Medusa/Nusy helmet. The +1 all skills bonus is worth more than the set bonus. Farm at RoA Until 180 Stay at Remains of Ancients until level 180. Well-geared players can kill in Hard Mode RoA by level 175. Killing snowmen or in Hector room drops 1-3 cubes for passive income, which also covers crafting materials later. Free vs Paid Powerlevels Avoid spending Rupees on powerlevels, but always take free ones. They're most impactful in the Smart Vendor Choices Sell ND (non-disassembleable) weapons and armor to vendors, but disassemble or altar dura gear. Crit power deco pieces from the altar are far more valuable than vendor rupees, especially before getting Lava gear. Gameplay Optimization Mechanic How It Works Gnoll Buff 30%/40%/50% damage reflection reduces damage taken by 3%/4%/5%. Very helpful buff for survivability in harder dungeons. Camper Title Reduces damage taken. Buy a tent from the merchant in hidden village to earn this title. Weapon Awakening Always awaken weapons and accessories with Awakening Stones. Keep weapons with the best bonus for future use. Universal Upgrades Priority Prioritize universal upgrades over class-specific gear (Lava Set, Helmet +24, Emblem, Yushiva Belt). You never know when you'll want to change classes. Purse Purchases Buy Purse of Bright Powers (non-pet classes) or Purse of Invocations (pet classes) for 500 Cash Shop coins - the bonus is worth the investment. Enhanced Crystal Glasses Cheap item equippable from level 1: +10 all stats, +40 luck. Get from AH for ~25M (drops from HRoA snowman Hector room). Get it ASAP. Arena Currency Once committed to a main, do daily Arena quests. 20k Arena points = Traveling Gear (4% all stats) from Arena Merchant Jana at Rondo. Worth the grind. RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Getting Started in Rappelz", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/getting-started/", "text": "Getting Started in Rappelz RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Getting Started in Rappelz Everything a new player needs: early leveling zones, buffs, quests and more. Starting Your Character If you have 0 Rupies on your account, follow these steps first. Note: It's recommended that you walk through the quests of Trainee Island to get a feel of the game the first time if you don't want to skip the initial steps outlined below. Initial Setup Teleport to Hidden Village and go to the merchant then sell everything in your bag. This will get you more than 7,000 Rupees needed for buffs and traveling to Moonlight Dungeon. Put Rupies in Warehouse and delete your character, then create a new one. Go to the Buffer NPC and take the free buff and the 7,000 Rupee Buff. Leveling Phases Level Range Location / Method Notes 1–10 Moonlight Dungeon Exterior Kill 3 mobs outside while using Stamina Saver and a growth potion. 10–50 Moonlight Dungeon Interior Continue leveling inside Moonlight Dungeon. 50 Class Change Teleport to Hidden Village and talk to the Class Master. If broke, sell Extreme Essence at the Flea Market. 50–105 Crystal Valley (Hard Mode) Find the Koala and enter Hard mode. Stay until level 105. Do your 2nd class change at the Class Master. 105–120 Red Farm or Witch Quest 1 RedFarm: Rondo Guild NPC | Witch Quest 1: Katan Guild NPC. Complete second class change first. 120–138 Sanctuary Questline Complete the Sanctuary questline. Quest starts at Rondo Merchant NPC. 138–150 Witch Quest 2 Quest starts at Horizon Hector NPC. 150–153 Master Class Trials Complete Master Class Trials. Quest starts at Hector. Self-Sufficient Progression If you don't want to rely on other players to progress: Go to Sanctuary Hidden and farm items with the [Witch] type because they have better stats. Take 120 items and make them +12 without breaking them, then attempt an Ancient Cube for a chance at getting +17. If you have full [Witch] equipment at level 120, all +12 or more, you will be stronger than anyone using level 150 gear at +7. This means your future characters will be able to skip Sanctuary quests entirely because you'll one-shot mobs in Sanctuary Hidden from level 105 to 133. What's Next? Once you reach level 153 and complete the Master Class Trials, you're ready for endgame progression. Head over to our Beyond Master Class guide to learn about gear requirements and strategies to push further. RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "How to Craft a Medal", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/how-to-craft-medal/", "text": "How to Craft a Medal ← Back to Home How to Craft a Medal Create an Ordinary Medal Combine one of the following to get a chance at crafting an Ordinary Medal: x1000 Naha's Basic Blueprints x500 Naha's Blueprints x100 Naha's Advanced Blueprints If it fails, you will receive 1 Medal Shard . Combining 10 Medal Shards will give you an Ordinary Medal . Alternatively, adding x1 Naha's Advanced Medal Shard to the combination will guarantee success . Identify the Medal To identify the medal, combine it with one of the following sets: x1 Philosopher's Scroll + x1 Secret Book or x1 Power of Change: Medal + x1 Secret Book Enhance the Medal Type Once identified, combine the medal with a gem to get an enhanced version: Health Gem → Enhanced Health Medal Strength Gem → Enhanced Strength Medal Intelligence Gem → Enhanced Intelligence Medal It is possible to re-identify Enhanced Medals using a Blessed Power of Change: Medal . Enchant the Medal All 4 medal types can be enchanted up to +32 Luciad Power . +0 to +20 requires a Medal Cube or the upgraded Ancient Medal Cube . If the enchantment fails, it can be repaired with an E-Repair Powder: Medal . To increase beyond +20, use Luciad's Power: Medal . Enchant Success Rates Level Medal Cube Ancient Medal Cube +1 100.00% 100.00% +2 100.00% 100.00% +3 100.00% 100.00% +4 100.00% 100.00% +5 88.80% 100.00% +6 76.10% 100.00% +7 63.40% 93.40% +8 50.70% 80.70% +9 44.40% 74.40% +10 38.00% 68.00% +11 31.70% 61.70% +12 25.30% 55.30% +13 19.00% 49.00% +14 15.20% 45.20% +15 12.70% 42.70% +16 11.40% 41.40% +17 10.10% 40.10% +18 8.80% 38.80% +19 7.60% 37.60% +20 6.30% 36.30% Medal Basic Stats Each medal type provides the following base stats regardless of enchantment level: Ordinary Medal +5% Basic Stats (Except Luck) Enhanced Health Medal +15% Max HP / Max MP +15% P. Def / M. Def +15% HP Recov. Enhanced Strength Medal +20% P. Atk. +20 Crit. Pow. Enhanced Intelligence Medal +20% M. Atk. +20 Crit. Pow."}, {"title": "How to Make Belt (8 Slots)", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/how-to-make-belt-8-slots/", "text": "How to Make Belt (8 Slots) ← Back to Home How to Make Belt (8 Slots) Guide to upgrading your belt from slot 5 up to slot 8 using the Ultimate Belt Upgrade Kit . ⚠ Important: The Ultimate Belt Upgrade Kit is only used for slots 5, 6, 7, and 8 . Lower slots (1–4) require the regular Belt Upgrade Kit , which can be purchased from a merchant in Hidden Village or dropped from mobs. Overview The Ultimate Belt Upgrade Kit is used to upgrade belts from slot 5 → slot 8 , one slot at a time. Requirements The belt you want to upgrade (placed in the target slot ) 1 × Ultimate Belt Upgrade Kit (placed in the material slot ) How It Works Place the belt in the target slot . Place 1 Ultimate Belt Upgrade Kit in the material slot . Attempt the upgrade. Result ✓ Success: The belt gains one additional slot."}, {"title": "How to Make a Level 2 Potion", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/how-to-make-lvl2-potion/", "text": "How to Make a Level 2 Potion ← Back to Home How to Make a Level 2 Potion Requirements 1 × Empty Level 2 Potion — dropped during certain events 1 × Level 190 Pet The Empty Level 2 Potion is not available from regular merchants — it is only obtainable as a drop from specific in-game events. How It Works When your pet reaches level 190 , it unlocks a Level 2 Creation skill. Make sure you have an Empty Level 2 Potion in your bag, then use that skill to fill it. ✓ Result: Level 2 Potion"}, {"title": "How to Make a Pure White Weapon / Shield", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/how-to-make-pure-white-weapon/", "text": "How to Make a Pure White Weapon / Shield ← Back to Home PATCH 9.8 How to Make a Pure White Weapon / Shield With patch 9.8 you can now obtain an upgrade for your weapons from the Island of Forgotten Gods and shields from Devildom . Crafting a Pure White Weapon / Shield Combine the following three items at the upgrade NPC: x1 Island of Forgotten Gods Weapon or Devildom Shield (your existing item) x1 Clean Circus Dungeon Weapon or Shield (same type) Pure Luciad’s Energy — 25 for a 1-handed weapon / shield • 50 for a 2-handed weapon Luciad’s Power — New Maximum Once upgraded, the maximum enchantment level via Luciad’s Power is increased from +32 to +40 . Range Material Required +0 → +32 Luciad’s Power (standard) +32 → +40 Luciad’s Advanced Cube — low drop chance from the new dungeon Upgrade Retention When upgrading your existing weapon or shield, everything is preserved : Enchantment level Awakening Random options Soulstones Weapon shards Requirement ⚠ Level 210 required. When upgrading to a Pure White Weapon or Shield, the level requirement to equip the item is raised to Level 210 ."}, {"title": "How to Move My Pets – Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/how-to-move-my-pets/", "text": "How to Move My Pets – Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home PETS How to Move My Pets Pet Controls Shift + Left Click — Move your pet only, without moving your character. Alt + Left Click — Send your pet to attack. RAPPELZ GUIDELINES — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "How to craft lava gear?", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/how-to-craft-lava-gear/", "text": "﻿ How to craft lava gear? ← Back How to craft lava gear? Table of Contents Pre-requisite Dungeon Difficulties How to Enter Drops From Lava Box Combinations Exchange with NPC Cash Items Materials Crafting Lava Weapons Crafting Equipment Crafting Wings Crafting Wings Stats Wings Enhancement Rate Advanced Wings Enhancement Rate Bonus Sets Lava Mask Crafting Lava Cloak Crafting Lava Cloak Stats Lava Cloak Enhancement Rate Pre-requisite You have to finish the \"Vulcanus\" Quest-Line and the first of the \"Ancient Koala\" Quest-Line (unlocks at lvl 175), to be able to receive the keys and enter the dungeon. The materials to craft the new Lava-Gear can be obtained from the Vulcanus dungeon east of Rondo, which can be entered after reaching level 200. Dungeon Difficulties Difficulty Required Level Easy 200+ Normal 210+ Hard 220+ How to Enter Item NPC Key Availability Limit Note Vulcano Secret Key Noblewoman Rani 24 Hours 10 per day You can buy more keys (not timed) from the cash shop. Drops Monster Drop Table Item Image lava drop lava box From Lava Box Item Image Typhon Shard Lava Physical Shard Lava Defence Shard Lava Magical Shard Combinations Item Image lava Cube Advanced lava Cube Typhon Crystal lava Feather Typhon Scroll Exchange with NPC Item lak Scroll Cash Items Item Image lava repair Kit Vulcanos secret Key Blessed Lava Feather Blessed Typhon Scroll Materials Crafting Item Materials Typhon crystal 1 Typhon shard + 20 x M.Atk Granting TP Card Pack (from Merchant, in Hidden Village for cheaper cost ) lava cube 1 lava drop + 1 Typhon crystal Advanced lava Cube 3 lava drops + 3 Typhon crystals Lava Feather 5 lava Drops + 5 Typhon Crystals Typhon Scroll 1000 lak Souls (Trade Lak for Lak Souls from a Lak trader in town) Lava Weapons Crafting Item Materials Lava Spear 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Behemoth's Spear Lava One-Handed Axe 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Demonic Axe Lava Two-Handed Axe 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Rhegium's Outlaw Lava One-Handed Mace 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Stroder's Blessing Lava Two-Handed Mace 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Hermes's Hammer Lava One-Handed Wand 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Mark's Stick Lava Two-Handed Wand 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Branium's Staff Lava Dagger 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Deadly Poison Dagger Lava Two-Handed Long Sword 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Bellatrix's Sword Lava One-Handed Long Sword 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Gladius Lava Long Bow 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Lartis's Bow Lava Crossbow 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Lycan's Cross bow Lava Shield 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Shield of Janua Lava Magic Shield 75 Lava Drops + 75 Typhon Crystals + Mirror of Janua Equipment Crafting Item Materials Lava Helmet 35 Lava Drops + 35 Typhon Crystals + Nusylites Helmet Lava Boots 35 Lava Drops + 35 Typhon Crystals + Nusylites Boots Lava Gloves 35 Lava Drops + 35 Typhon Crystals + Nusylites Gloves Lava Armor 35 Lava Drops + 35 Typhon Crystals + Nusylites Armor Wings Crafting Item Materials Lava Physical Wings 100 Lava Drops + 500 White Steel + 350 Lava Physical Shard + 100 Typhon Crystals Lava Magic Wings 100 Lava Drops + 500 White Steel + 350 Lava Magical Shard + 100 Typhon Crystals Lava Defence Wings 100 Lava Drops + 500 White Steel + 350 Lava Defence Shard + 100 Typhon Crystals Advanced Lava Wings Lava Physical Wings +10 + Lava Magic Wings +10 + Lava Defence Wings +10 + 100 Typhon Crystals Lava Stats Wings Stats Physical Upgrade P.ATK Move.SPD Creature DMG Reduction Additional Stats Enhancement Item +1 1% 50 1% 1% Lava Cube +2 2% 50 2% 1% Lava Cube +3 3% 50 3% 2% Lava Cube +4 4% 50 4% 2% Lava Cube +5 5% 50 5% 3% Lava Cube +6 6% 50 6% 3% Lava Cube +7 7% 50 7% 4% Lava Cube +8 8% 50 8% 4% Lava Cube +9 9% 50 9% 5% Lava Cube +10 10% 50 10% 5% Lava Cube Magical Upgrade M.ATK Move.SPD Creature DMG Reduction Additional Stats Enhancement Item +1 1% 50 1% 1% Lava Cube +2 2% 50 2% 1% Lava Cube +3 3% 50 3% 2% Lava Cube +4 4% 50 4% 2% Lava Cube +5 5% 50 5% 3% Lava Cube +6 6% 50 6% 3% Lava Cube +7 7% 50 7% 4% Lava Cube +8 8% 50 8% 4% Lava Cube +9 9% 50 9% 5% Lava Cube +10 10% 50 10% 5% Lava Cube Defense Upgrade Max HP/MP P.def/M.def Move.SPD Creature DMG Reduction Additional Stats Enhancement Item +1 1% 1% 50 1% 1% Lava Cube +2 2% 2% 50 2% 1% Lava Cube +3 3% 3% 50 3% 2% Lava Cube +4 4% 4% 50 4% 2% Lava Cube +5 5% 5% 50 5% 3% Lava Cube +6 6% 6% 50 6% 3% Lava Cube +7 7% 7% 50 7% 4% Lava Cube +8 8% 8% 50 8% 4% Lava Cube +9 9% 9% 50 9% 5% Lava Cube +10 10% 10% 50 10% 5% Lava Cube Wings Enhancement Rate Level Rate +1 30% +2 25% +3 20% +4 15% +5 10% +6 9% +7 8% +8 7% +9 6% +10 5% Advanced Wings Stats Upgrade M.ATK + P.ATK + Max HP+Max MP+M.def+P.def Move.SPD Creature DMG Reduction Additional Stats Enhancement Item Base 10% 50 10% 5% Advanced Lava Cube +1 11% 50 11% 6% Advanced Lava Cube +2 12% 50 12% 6% Advanced Lava Cube +3 13% 50 13% 7% Advanced Lava Cube +4 14% 50 14% 7% Advanced Lava Cube +5 15% 50 15% 8% Advanced Lava Cube +6 16% 50 16% 8% Advanced Lava Cube +7 17% 50 17% 9% Advanced Lava Cube +8 18% 50 18% 9% Advanced Lava Cube +9 19% 50 19% 10% Advanced Lava Cube +10 20% 50 20% 10% - Advanced Wings Enhancement Rate Level Rate +1 10.0% +2 9.0% +3 8.0% +4 7.0% +5 6.0% +6 5.0% +7 5.0% +8 5.0% +9 5.0% +10 5.0% The basic wings can be enhanced with Lava cubes and the Adv. Wings can be enhanced with Adv. Lava Cubes. If the enhancement of the Wings fail, the wings will NOT break but the invested Lava Cube will be lost. Bonus Sets If you have one of the new weapons (shields and Magewalls are not considered as weapons) , the armor, the helmet, the boots, the gloves and one of the 4 new wings equipped you gain the first set bonus: +10% critical power +15% max hp reduces dmg received from pets by 10% Lava Mask Crafting Material Amount lava drop 300 Typhon Crystal 300 Soul Bead of White Dragon 100 Lava Physical Shard 1000 Lava Magical Shard 1000 Lava Deffence Shard 1000 Lava Cloak Crafting Material Amount lava drop 300 Typhon Crystal 300 Soul Bead of Black Dragon 100 Lava Physical Shard 1000 Lava Magical Shard 1000 Lava Deffence Shard 1000 Lava Mask Stats 5% all stats Lava Cloak Stats Upgrade Max HP & MP M.ATK & P.ATK Mov.SPD DMG To Devil DMG Reduction from Devil Base 5% 5% 20 1% 1% +1 6% 6% 20 2% 2% +2 7% 7% 20 4% 4% +3 8% 8% 20 6% 6% +4 9% 9% 20 8% 8% +5 10% 10% 20 10% 10% +6 11% 11% 20 12% 12% +7 12% 12% 20 14% 15% +8 13% 13% 20 16% 20% +9 14% 14% 20 18% 25% +10 15% 15% 20 20% 30% Lava Cloak Enhancement Rate Level Rate with normal feather With Blessed Lava Feather +1 20% 25% +2 15% 20% +3 10% 15% +4 5% 10% +5 4% 9% +6 3% 8% +7 3% 8% +8 3% 8% +9 3% 8% +10 3% 8% The mask and the cloak will give you the second set bonus: DMG All Types: 10% DMG Reduce All Types: 5% To enhance the cloak you need the Lava Feather's. If this enhancement fails, the cloak will break and you need to repair it with an \"Lava repair kit\" which can be obtained from the cash shop."}, {"title": "Luciad's Power & Enchantment Guide", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/what-is-plus24-16-32-40-40/", "text": "Luciad's Power & Enchantment Guide ← Back to Home Luciad’s Power & Enchantment Guide Enchantment above +20 has changed. Existing equipment at +21 and higher was converted automatically — stats remain the same. Reaching +20 When a Rank 7 piece of equipment reaches +20 , it gains x1 Luciad’s Power . Increasing Further (Beyond +20) To increase stats past +20, combine: Luciad’s Power Stone: Weapon or Luciad’s Power Stone: Armor Luciad’s Pure Cube — drops from all bosses level 150 or above Combination — using Luciad’s Power Stone + Luciad’s Pure Cube Obtaining Luciad’s Power Stones Luciad’s Power Stones are obtained by extracting Luciad’s Power from a +20 food item using a Luciad’s Power Extractor (purchased from the Smithy for 200,000,000 Rupees ). Extraction rules: One Extractor is needed per 1 Luciad’s Power stored in the equipment. 32 Luciad’s Power stored = 32 Extractors needed. The equipment used to extract will be destroyed after extraction. You can only extract the full amount of Luciad’s Power stored — partial extraction is not possible. Extraction — converting a +20 food item into a Luciad’s Power Stone Enchantment Changes Overview Summary of enchantment changes"}, {"title": "Pet Farm Guide", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/pet-farm/", "text": "Pet Farm Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Pet Farm Here you can find details about the changes introduced to the Pet Farm on 21/07/2020. Experience Rates As an example, a 190+ pet which is placed in the farm for 12 hours with the basic pass will gain 15% . If using the Premium Pass it will gain 60% . Using a Creature Farm Cracker will increase the exp earned by 100% . RAPPELZ GUIDELINES — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Pet Taming", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/pet-taming/", "text": "Pet Taming RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Pet Taming In order to increase your pet taming chance, there are multiple items you need to acquire. Each one increases your taming chance by +1% . Taming Chance Items Item Bonus Image Enhanced Glasses +1% Taming Crystal Sword +1% Taming Emblem +1% Taming Luciad's Iron Mask +1% Taming Taming Rings from Circus (x2) +2 Taming Skill (each) Bear Belt +1 Taming Skill DT Buff +1 Taming Skill — Helmet +24 +3 Taming Skill — Vulcano Boss Card Collection +1 Taming Skill RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Rupee Farming", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/rupee-farming/", "text": "Rupee Farming RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Rupee Farming There are different ways to farm rupees in the game. Snow Basin — Kill dragons and sell Lucky Cubes at the Flea Market. Farming at Lake Kaia or Pig's Spot . The Farming Principle The principle of farming is very simple: the more Luck stat you have, the more drops you get. This is why Beast Master is the best class to farm rupees — its skill Harmony of Life allows you to transform into your summoned pet and gain bonus stats, including Luck . Try taming Unique Humans in the Parallel World dungeon and stage the one you get as a tank pet (it has the highest stats). Then you can summon 2 Wind Pixies S0 Lv160, equipped with 2H Maces + Shield. Target Setup for Farming Slot Item / Pet Main Pet Human Tank S5 (you can start with an S0 or any pet just to get going) Summons 2 Wind Pixies Lv160 — for better gear equipment options Helmet Enhanced Glasses Rings +40 Luck Rings x2 (droppable at Lake Kaia) Armor Set Ergon Set — droppable in Ancient Magic Lab (Fanatics) or the stone golems during the master class trials : gives 10% Luck Wings Luminous Feather (+50 Luck) Belt Pets 2x Snowman S0 Lv90 + 2x Kenta S0 Lv90 Weapons 2x Royal Axe (dropped in Lost Mines) Luck Titles Lucky Potion Best Wishes Boss Card Buff 5B Buff from other players — provides more stats to you and your pets, including more Luck. You'll earn back the 5B in 2 to 3 hours, then use Refresh Scrolls on yourself and your pets. This step is not mandatory, but I highly recommend it! Example of total Luck on BM: Playstyle Your Beast Master will be running through mobs — they will keep dying before you even reach them, because the 2 Wind Pixies auto-attack from range. Perma running, no stopping, easier looting. RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "What is the Maximum Attack Speed? – Rappelz Guidelines", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/what-is-maximum-attack-speed/", "text": "What is the Maximum Attack Speed? – Rappelz Guidelines RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home COMBAT What is the Maximum Attack Speed? As of Epic 9.6 , how attack speed affects the number of attacks per second has been reworked, removing the plateaus and giving a smoother increase. RAPPELZ GUIDELINES — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "What to Do at Level 105", "cat": "Guide", "url": "guide/faq/what-to-do-at-105/", "text": "What to Do at Level 105 ← Back to Home What to Do at Level 105 New to the game? Check out the Getting Started guide for a full overview of leveling phases, quests, and what to do from level 1 to Master Class — including the level 105 section. For more details on the quests available at level 105, check the dedicated channel in the official Discord below. 💬 OFFICIAL DISCORD For a detailed and up-to-date walkthrough of everything to do at level 105, check the dedicated channel in the official Discord: ↗ Open in Discord — #level-105-guide channel"}, {"title": "Lake Kaia Zone Guide", "cat": "Map", "url": "map/lake-kaia/", "text": "Lake Kaia Zone Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Lake Kaia Map How to Get There To teleport to Lake Kaia, teleport to the Devildom dungeon by talking to the Dungeon Teleporter NPC in any city. How to Farm Equip all your luck gear (see Rupee Farming Guide ) and just keep killing mobs. Once your bag is full, go back to town and sell everything to an NPC. Repeat! RAPPELZ GUIDELINES — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Pig's Spot Zone Guide", "cat": "Map", "url": "map/pigs-spot/", "text": "Pig's Spot Zone Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Pig's Spot Map How to Get There To teleport to Pig's Spot, talk to the Teleporter NPC in Hidden Village and choose Frozen Marduka Outpost , then run to the location shown in the map above. How to Farm Equip all your luck gear (see Rupee Farming Guide ) and just keep killing mobs. Once your bag is full, go back to town and sell everything to an NPC. Repeat! RAPPELZ GUIDELINES — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Remains of the Ancients", "cat": "Map", "url": "map/remains-of-the-ancients/", "text": "Remains of the Ancients RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Remains of the Ancients With the release of Epic 9.3 a new dungeon was added: “Remains of the Ancients”. Along with two new TP Quests, both of which can be started at 160. However, one can only be completed once the player has reached level 170. After reaching level 160, players can accept a quest from Warrior Hector in City of Ruins which begins a series of quests allowing them to enter the Remains of the Ancients. However, the final quest can only be completed once the player reaches 170 and returns to Warrior Hector. After completing this quest, players will receive an additional TP point. Quest Walkthrough Head to Rondo to find Armor Trader Bella. Kill Lilith in stage 3 or 4 of the Red Spider Circus to acquire a Bright Piece of Fabric (this may take a few attempts) and give it to Armor Trader Bella. Once you hand in the Fabric you will be given a Cute Doll. Head back to City of Ruins (you won’t be given a quest) and talk to Witch’s Child Xabi who is located right next to Warrior Hector. Accept that quest then talk to her again to turn it in (she takes the Cute Doll from you). Talk to Warrior Hector again before heading to Mare Village to talk with Charmer Kisha. Accept the quest from her and kill a Starving Slaughter, which can be found wandering around outside Mare Village. Return to Charmer Kisha and turn the quest in, accept her new quest and head back to Warrior Hector in City of Ruins. Accept his quest and head to the Red Spider Circus again. Kill Soul of Lunacy in either stages 3 or 4 and acquire the Remaining Trace (this could take a few attempts like Lilith). After acquiring the Remaining Trace, return to Warrior Hector. Talk to Witch’s Child Xabi, accept her quest and she will give you a Defense Force Token — this item will allow you to enter the Remains of the Ancients. Finally talk to Hector again to accept the last part of the quest; you will be tasked with acquiring a Bloody Report from Grandmaster Hector in the Remains of the Ancients. Once this part has been completed, if you have not yet reached level 170 Hector will no longer have anything to say to you. After reaching 170 and returning to Hector you will be able to finish this quest line and receive an additional TP. Dungeon Map RAPPELZ GUIDELINES — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "SnowBasin Zone Guide", "cat": "Map", "url": "map/snowbasin/", "text": "SnowBasin Zone Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home SnowBasin Map How to Get There To teleport to SnowBasin, talk to the Teleporter NPC in Hidden Village. Instances SnowBasin has 2 instances: Instance 1 — The area you arrive at when you teleport in. Lower level mobs suitable for leveling from 153 to 160. Instance 2 — Accessed by taking the portal where you first teleported in. Higher level mobs, harder difficulty. Mainly for players 190+. Benefits of This Zone Farming Lucky Cubes and White Steel Leveling pets Leveling from 153 to 160 Taming White Dragons RAPPELZ GUIDELINES — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Bloodthirsty Slaughterer Guide", "cat": "Pet", "url": "pet/bloodthirsty-slaughterer.html", "text": "Bloodthirsty Slaughterer Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Bloodthirsty Slaughterer About Bloodthirsty Slaughterer Can be tamed in Hidden RoA ( Remains of the Ancients map ). While it's not used by pet classes, its unity + encouragement is the best for all Melee classes (+200% strength for 30 seconds is an amazing boost). End game players stack BS pet on formation just to keep cycling through encouragements. Best pet for: Slayer , Berserker , WK . Skills RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide · Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher Content is community-sourced. Contribute corrections via the Discord."}, {"title": "Crystal Golem Guide", "cat": "Pet", "url": "pet/crystal-golem.html", "text": "Crystal Golem Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Crystal Golem About Crystal Golem Can be tamed in Hidden RoA ( Remains of the Ancients map ). This pet is used by Master Breeders as a tank since it synergizes well with Potency (main skill of Master Breeder). It's also used by Marksman since the unity provides Vita / Dex and Pdef, everything the class needs. Skills RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide · Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher Content is community-sourced. Contribute corrections via the Discord."}, {"title": "Crystal Spider Guide", "cat": "Pet", "url": "pet/crystal-spider.html", "text": "Crystal Spider Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Crystal Spider About Crystal Spider Can be tamed in RoA ( Remains of the Ancients map ). This is a cheap version of Hector. Can be used with a combination of a Wind Pixie for Overlord at early phase of the game, but it will be replaced soon with a 2nd Wind Pixie. Ideal for: no one! Skills RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide · Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher Content is community-sourced. Contribute corrections via the Discord."}, {"title": "Death Gladiator Guide", "cat": "Pet", "url": "pet/death-gladiator.html", "text": "Death Gladiator Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Death Gladiator About Death Gladiator Can be tamed in: Rondo Citadel DD6 after you kill Reviac DG in Citadel has higher chance to be tamed but it's harder to get into Citadel since it's a guild activity once per week. This pet has the best belt bonuses a melee class can dream of (STR, PATK, Agility, Evasion) all maxed in 3 slots allowing for more flexibility, thus why it's the most expensive pet today considering how rare it is to be tamed. The class that uses DG today is Beast Master thanks to Harmony of Life synergy. Skills RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide · Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher Content is community-sourced. Contribute corrections via the Discord."}, {"title": "Ethereal Pixie Guide", "cat": "Pet", "url": "pet/ethereal-pixie.html", "text": "Ethereal Pixie Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Ethereal Pixie About Ethereal Pixie Can be tamed in Laksy Field (east of Laksy’s Anchor) where you used to tame Red pixies and Blue pixies a century ago! This pet shines when it's stage 5, with the unique toggle Elemental Harmony that allows even melee players who lack survivability to pick her over Bloodthirsty Slaughterer. You'll see Master Breeder playing with 2 of those or a combination of CG + EP as the perfect combo thanks to Potency skill. Ideal for: Corruptor , Void Mage (Wind Pixie is better if you can't tank), Slayer , Berserker , Mercenary , Cardinal , Oracle , and Master Breeder . Important: This pet is not used for farming rupees. Skills RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide · Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher Content is community-sourced. Contribute corrections via the Discord."}, {"title": "Forest Pixie Guide", "cat": "Pet", "url": "pet/forest-pixie.html", "text": "Forest Pixie Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Forest Pixie About Forest Pixie Can be tamed in Fairy Woods (see images of Fairy Woods below). This pet is used as a belt pet for Deadeyes (4 x s5). Skills RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide · Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher Content is community-sourced. Contribute corrections via the Discord."}, {"title": "Grandmaster Hector Guide", "cat": "Pet", "url": "pet/grandmaster-hector.html", "text": "Grandmaster Hector Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Grandmaster Hector About Grandmaster Hector Can be tamed in Hidden RoA ( Remains of the Ancients map ). This pet performs very good in Devildom with Overlord but now it's just there for the Potion lvl 2. Hector potion is ideal for WK and Magus . Skills RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide · Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher Content is community-sourced. Contribute corrections via the Discord."}, {"title": "Wind Pixie Guide", "cat": "Pet", "url": "pet/wind-pixie.html", "text": "Wind Pixie Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Wind Pixie About Wind Pixie Can be tamed in Fairy Woods (see images of Fairy Woods below). This is the most used pet in the game thanks to the flat Int and Agility it provides through unity, potion, and encouragement. It's a physical melee pet (but attacks from short range) — logical, right? Ideal for: Slayer (if you can't tank), Deadeye , VM (if you can't tank), Overlord . If you are looking for a pet to farm at Lake Kaia or Pigs as a pet class, this is the one! Skills RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide · Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher Content is community-sourced. Contribute corrections via the Discord."}, {"title": "Gnoll Buff Strategy", "cat": "Strategy", "url": "strategy/gnoll-buff/", "text": "Gnoll Buff Strategy RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Gnoll Buff Strategy ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ GUIDELINES — Fan-made community guide"}, {"title": "Legendary Gear Strategy", "cat": "Strategy", "url": "strategy/legendary-gear/", "text": "Legendary Gear Strategy RAPPELZ GUIDELINES ← Back to Home ← Back to Home Legendary Gear Strategy ⚠ In Progress - This guide is being updated. RAPPELZ GUIDELINES — Fan-made community guide"},{"title":"Alcatraz Dungeon Guide","cat":"Guide","url":"guide/alcatraz/","text":"Alcatraz Dungeon Guide - Rappelz Codex RAPPELZ CODEX Back to Home Back to Home Epic Dungeon Guide Alcatraz Lv 228-230 Marduka Watchtower 8 Difficulties 1-8 Players A high-level Epic dungeon. The Butcher Vulcan has led a prison break threatening Gaia - rally the guilds and retake Alcatraz. Unlock it via the questline from Guard Captain Kudun in Rondo (Lv 228); enter through Sorcerer Kael at the Marduka Watchtower (Lv 230). Table of Contents Dungeon Entrance Difficulty and Player Modes Dungeon Monsters Loot and Drops Accessory Enchanting Imbuement Eraser Sapphire Transfer Scroll Boss Card Collection Main Questline Daily and Weekly Quests Dungeon Entrance Enter through the Marduka Watchtower via Sorcerer Kael . Talk to him to create the instance and pick your Player Mode. Marduka Watchtower - Dungeon Entrance Difficulty and Player Modes Pick a Player Mode at the entrance. It sets the max players and which stages you can run - each stage cleared gives its matching Bonus Chest . Fewer players than the cap = better rewards. Mode S1 S2 S3 S4 S5 S6 S7 S8 Bonus Chests 1 Player - - - - 1, 2, 4, 5 2 Players - - - - 1, 2, 3, 5 4 Players - - - - 2, 3, 4, 5 8 Players - - - - 2, 3, 5, 6 Player limit is enforced - extra players are removed from the instance. Beating the final boss has a chance to drop extra bonus loot. Dungeon Monsters Every stage uses the same enemies - only their level rises with the stage. You'll fight waves of prison mobs plus three mini-bosses and the final boss. Regular Mobs Brutal, Cunning, Crazy, Chain, Cursed, Furious and Vengeful Prisoners, Prisoner of Darkness, Herald of Darkness, Follower of Pain, Cursed Soul, Summoned Prisoner. Bosses Karmos Saragorn Necron mini-bosses, then the final boss Butcher Vulcan . Level of each monster in every stage (all regular prisoners share the same level per stage): Monster S1 S2 S3 S4 S5 S6 S7 S8 Regular Prisoners 240 245 250 250 255 258 260 265 Karmos 240 255 260 260 265 263 270 275 Saragorn 250 255 260 260 265 263 270 275 Necron 250 255 260 260 265 263 270 275 Summoned Prisoner 250 255 260 260 265 263 270 275 Butcher Vulcan 260 265 270 270 270 269 275 280 Karmos, Saragorn and Necron are the mini-bosses (red); Butcher Vulcan is the final boss (gold). Loot and Drops Loot depends on whether you defeat normal monsters or bosses . Normal monsters provide materials and progression items, while each boss also drops unique equipment, crafting materials, and its own Boss Card. Normal Monster Rewards Every normal monster in Alcatraz has a chance to drop: Item Quantity Mithril Ore 1-2 Skill Card Box: Master 1-2 Luciad Medal 1 Rank 7 Cube Group 1 The maximum quantity of Mithril Ore and Skill Card Boxes increases in later stages. Boss Rewards Each boss has its own exclusive rewards in addition to common materials. All bosses drop a Mithril Ingot and their own Boss Card . Karmos The Bloodthirsty Beast Boss Card: Bloodthirsty Beast, Karmos x1 Mithril Earrings of Bloodlust x1 Karmos's Blood-Tainted Fang x1 Mithril Ingot x1 Saragorn The Dark Alchemist Boss Card: Dark Alchemist, Saragorn x1 Mithril Necklace of Corruption x1 Saragorn's Alembic Vial x1 Mithril Ingot x1 Necron The Shadow of the Reaper Boss Card: Shadow of the Reaper, Necron x1 Mithril Ring of Shadows x1 Necron's Shadow Shard x1 Mithril Ingot x1 Butcher Vulcan Final Boss drops all three accessories Boss Card: Butcher Vulcan x1 Mithril Ring of Shadows x1 Mithril Necklace of Corruption x1 Mithril Earrings of Bloodlust x1 Vulcan's Soul Spark x1 Vulcan's Cinder x1 Mithril Ingot x1 Boss rewards stay the same across all stages. Progressing to higher stages primarily increases the quantity of normal monster drops , making later stages better for farming materials. Accessory Enchanting Enchanting Alcatraz accessories follows the same principle as Sky Accessories . Slot Requirement Main Slot The accessory you want to enchant Material Slot Stat Essence x (target enchant x 10) Material Slot Imbuement Ore or Blessed Imbuement Ore x 1 Essence cost example: going from +9 to +10 requires 100 Stat Essence (10 x 10). Base accessories can be enchanted up to +10 . Enhanced versions can go up to +15 . Success Rates Base accessories can be enchanted up to +10 ; enhanced versions reach +15 . Blessed Imbuement Ore gives far better odds at high levels. Enchant Imbuement Ore Blessed Imbuement Ore +1 100% 100% +2 70% 100% +3 60% 90% +4 50% 80% +5 40% 70% +6 30% 60% +7 20% 50% +8 15% 45% +9 10% 40% +10 8% 38% +11 (enhanced) 6% 36% +12 (enhanced) 5% 35% +13 (enhanced) 5% 35% +14 (enhanced) 5% 35% +15 (enhanced) 5% 35% +11 to +15 are only reachable on Enhanced accessories. Alcatraz Imbuement Eraser The Alcatraz Imbuement Eraser removes only the applied Imbuement Essence , so you can swap to a different stat while keeping the accessory, its enhancements, and its Awakening intact. Alcatraz Imbuement Eraser Using the Imbuement Eraser Enhanced Mithril Accessories On an Enhanced Mithril Accessory , the Eraser removes the Imbuement Essence but reverts the accessory to Enhanced Mithril +0 . Erasing an Enhanced Mithril Accessory Sapphire Transfer Scroll The Sapphire Transfer Scroll lets you transfer a Sapphire Ring, Earring, or Necklace into a new accessory. Speak to Blacksmith Elara outside Alcatraz. Blacksmith Elara - found outside Alcatraz Requirements The Sapphire Transfer Scroll in your inventory. The Sapphire Ring / Earring / Necklace you want to transfer equipped . Combination materials in your inventory: 50 Mithril Ore + 1 accessory-specific item : Necron's Shadow Shard Karmos's Blood-Tainted Fang Saragorn's Alembic Vial How to Transfer Talk to Blacksmith Elara outside Alcatraz and choose \"Sapphire Transfer\" from the menu. You'll only be shown equipped accessories eligible for transfer. To avoid mistakes, only equip the one you want transferred. Click the accessory you wish to transfer and confirm. Selecting the accessory to transfer Only equipped , eligible accessories appear in the list. Confirming the transfer Example - result after transfer Boss Card Collection Each boss has a chance to drop its own Boss Card . Collect the required number and trade them to the Black Marketer Nostra Family NPC for a stronger Collection Card . Boss Cards and Effects Equip a Boss Card for these effects. Note that most carry a drawback alongside their bonuses. Necron Shadow of the Reaper pet build Breeder's Synergy, Domestication, Unholy Synergy +5 levels Creature Mastery +7 levels Creature HP and MP Expansion +5 levels Creature Control -2 levels Saragorn Dark Alchemist damage / drops P. Atk and M. Atk +10% Luck +30 Chance to raise drop rate when attacking HP / MP -50% Karmos Bloodthirsty Beast tank Vitality +10% Max HP +20% Chance for Devil's Restoration when attacking Strength / Intelligence -15% P. Atk and M. Atk -10% Butcher Vulcan Final boss offense P. Pierce and M. Pierce +20% Critical Power +110 Incoming damage +5% Collection Card Exchange Trade Boss Cards to the Black Marketer for these permanent Collection Cards: Collection Card Bonus Rarity Cards Needed Necron, Shadow of the Reaper Strength / Intelligence +50 Epic 2 Saragorn, Dark Alchemist Crit Rate +10% P. Atk and M. Atk +450 Unique 3 Karmos, Bloodthirsty Beast Vitality +50 Max HP +2,000 Unique 3 Butcher Vulcan P. Pierce and M. Pierce +500 Crit Power +30 Epic 2 Main Questline Starts at Lv 228 in Rondo, runs through the guild cities, and unlocks the dungeon at Lv 230 . # Quest Lv Start NPC (City) Objective 1 The Guards' Tension 228 Guard Captain Kudun (Rondo) Talk to Guard Captain Kudun 2 A Threat to the Kingdom of Gaia 228 Guard Captain Kudun (Rondo) Talk to Mayor Ailrena in Rondo 3 Begging For Help 228 Mayor Ailrena (Rondo) Talk to Guild Official Resha in Rondo 4 Recruitment of Mercenaries (1) 228 Guild Official Resha (Rondo) Talk to Guild Official Oveli in Horizon 5 Recruitment of Mercenaries (2) 228 Guild Official Oveli (Horizon) Talk to Guild Official Leviathan in Katan 6 Recruitment of Mercenaries (3) 228 Guild Official Leviathan (Katan) Talk to Guild Official Ces in Laksy 7 Good News 228 Guild Official Ces (Laksy) Talk to Guard Captain Kudun in Rondo 8 Delivery to Alcatraz 228 Guard Captain Kudun (Rondo) Deliver the letter to Sorcerer Kael at Marduka Watchtower 9 Clear The Way (1) 230 Sorcerer Kael (Watchtower) Kill Karmos, the Bloodthirsty Beast 10 Clear The Way (2) 230 Sorcerer Kael (Watchtower) Kill Saragorn, the Dark Alchemist 11 Vulcan's Right Hand 230 Sorcerer Kael (Watchtower) Kill Necron, the Shadow of the Reaper 12 Vulcan's Fate 230 Sorcerer Kael (Watchtower) Kill The Butcher Vulcan 13 The Guardians' Request (1-8) 230 Sorcerer Kael (Watchtower) Kill The Butcher Vulcan in each Stage (1 through 8) 500 AP each Daily and Weekly Quests Repeatable quests from Sorcerer Kael at the Marduka Watchtower. All reward Mithril Ingot . Type Quest Objective Reward Daily Helping the Guards Kill x5 Butcher Vulcan (Stages 1, 2, 3) Mithril Ingot x1 Daily Helping the Guards [2] Kill x5 Butcher Vulcan (Stages 4, 5, 6) Mithril Ingot x1 Weekly Defending the Kingdom Kill x25 Butcher Vulcan (Stages 1, 2, 3) Mithril Ingot x5 Weekly Defending the Kingdom [2] Kill x25 Butcher Vulcan (Stages 4, 5, 6) Mithril Ingot x5 Weekly Defending the Kingdom [3] Kill x5 Butcher Vulcan (Stages 7, 8) Mithril Ingot x5 RAPPELZ CODEX Fan-made community guide Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher"},{"title":"Devildom Dungeon Guide","cat":"Guide","url":"guide/devildom/","text":"Devildom Dungeon Guide - Rappelz Codex RAPPELZ CODEX Back to Home Back to Home Dungeon Guide Devildom Lv 175+ Kaia Lake 60 Rooms 6 Stages Devildom is a dungeon for players who are at least level 175. Complete the Ice Maiden quest line first, then the friendly Marduka Nakibu will offer a short quest line that unlocks dungeon access. Located in the centre of Kaia Lake . Table of Contents Dungeon Structure Stages and Bosses Stage Warps Drops and Equipment Yushiva's Belt Set Bonus Crystals and Beads Blacksmith Tarun Armor Progression Upgrade Tables Scales and Orbs Cloaks Job Type Note Dungeon Structure Devildom is made up of 60 rooms split across 6 stages , each harder than the last. You must kill all monsters in a room before moving to the next. Stages and Bosses Stages 1 3 have fixed boss spawns. Stages 4 5 and Stage 6's first room each have a 50% chance to spawn the default pair or the Main Boss + Yushiva. Stage 6's final room is always a fixed multi-boss encounter. 1 Stage 1 Spirit Mini: Gargam the Cursed Ent Main: Hispo the Abomination 2 Stage 2 Spirit Mini: Rayash the Bloody Main: Kleinkacmo the Marduka King 3 Stage 3 Spirit Mini: Kraken of Infinity Main: Yushiva 4 Stage 4 Undead Mecca Antique (Bosses) First: Ancestral Elder + Wooden Devil or Wooden Devil + Yushiva Final: Ancestral Hispo + Gorg the Slaughter or Gorg the Slaughter + Yushiva 5 Stage 5 Beast Ain Antique (Bosses) First: Ancestral Rayash + Blargon the Antique Gargoyle or Blargon + Yushiva Final: Ancestral Kleinkacmo + Magma Golem or Magma Golem + Yushiva 6 Stage 6 Final Stage Dragon Devil Antique (Bosses) First (50%): Ancestral Kraken of Infinite + Reviac's Golem or Reviac's Golem + Yushiva Final: Ancestral Wooden Devil, Ancestral Gorg, Ancestral Blargon, Ancestral Magma Golem, Reviac's Champion and Reviac: Master of Devildom After defeating Reviac, 4 Death Gladiators Human also spawn. Stage Warps and NPC Nuz Complete a quest for each stage from Nuz (outside the dungeon) to unlock direct warping. You arrive in the stage's Lobby talk to the stone inside to enter. Party members can run through stages they haven't unlocked yet when following someone who has. Drops and Equipment Overview Item Type Level Req. Shield of Janua Shield 175 Mirror of Janua Magewall 175 Yushiva's Blue Necklace Accessory 175 Yushiva's Red Earrings Accessory 175 10 New Belts Belt 175 3 New Cloaks Cloak 190 Nusylite's Set Armor Set 175 Fluminis's Set Armor Set 181 185 Inferno Set Armor Set 186 190 Reviac Set Armor Set 191 195 Yushiva's Belt Grants +30 Critical Power and +1 level to all Skills (excluding TP skills). Provides damage bonuses vs. specific monster types depending on the Belt Stone applied. Default: +20% damage dealt to Spirit type 20% damage received from Spirit type. With Belt Stone (Cash Shop): +20% dealt to Spirits + one extra type 10% received from those two types. Belt Stone Variants Each stone changes the secondary monster type bonus. Default belt icon shown left, stone icon right. Belt: Angel Belt: Mortal Belt: Devil Belt: Undead Belt: Beast Belt: Ain Belt: Mecca Belt: Dragon Belt: Insect Belt: Antique Belt Crafting Materials Very low drop chance from any Yushiva boss. Can also be crafted: Material Amount Ice Maiden's Essence 50 White Dragon's Soul Bead 500 Black Dragon's Soul Bead 300 Sand Dragon's Soul Bead 200 White Steel 500 Refined Crystal of Devildom 500 +0 Bear Skin Belt 1 Yushiva's Accessories Set Bonus Equipping both Yushiva's Necklace and Yushiva's Red Earrings grants a set bonus, further enhanced when also wearing a Yushiva's Belt . Crystals and Soul Beads All mobs and bosses can drop Black Crystal Boxes and Spirit Bead Boxes . Black Crystal Box 1 Crystal of Devildom. Collect 100 to craft 1 Refined Crystal (double-click to combine). Spirit Bead Box 1 random Soul Bead: White Dragon's Soul Bead most common Black Dragon's Soul Bead relatively common Sand Dragon's Soul Bead rare Blacksmith Tarun Find Blacksmith Tarun in Katan to craft all Devildom armor sets. Tarun can also open Black Crystal Boxes in bulk and sells the Medusa's Shaper converts any r7 helmet into a Medusa's Helm (required for all Devildom helm crafts), letting you transfer your enchantment levels to the new helmet. Armor Set Progression Nusylite's Lv 175 Fluminis's Lv 181 185 Inferno Lv 186 190 Reviac Lv 191 195 Best Nusylite's Requires Parallel World equipment enhanced with a Distorted Space's Armor Upgrade Stone . Fluminis's Requires only Refined Crystals of Devildom. Inferno Requires Soul Beads + Scales of Devildom + Refined Crystals. Reviac Requires Soul Beads + Devil Orbs + Refined Crystals. Upgrading armor, gloves, or boots individually breaks the Parallel World set bonus . Upgrade all three at the same time if possible. You also need to upgrade a Medusa's Helm to Nusylite's to maintain the full set effect. Upgrade Tables Nusylite's and Fluminis's Item Lv Additional Stat Refined Crystal Nusylite's Helmet 175 Evasion / M. Res +1% 50 Nusylite's Gloves 175 Atk / Cast Speed +10 50 Nusylite's Boots 175 Movement Speed +10 50 Nusylite's Armor 175 All stats (ex. Luck) +30 50 Total Full Nusylite's Set 200 Fluminis's Helmet 181 Evasion / M. Res +3% 130 Fluminis's Gloves 182 Atk / Cast Speed +12 150 Fluminis's Boots 183 Movement Speed +12 220 Fluminis's Armor 185 All stats (ex. Luck) +40 300 Total Full Fluminis's Set 800 Inferno and Reviac Full Crafting Armor Lv Base Refined Crystal White Bead Black Bead Sand Bead Scale of Devildom Devil Orb Inferno Set Lv 186 190 Inferno's Helmet 186 Fluminis' Helmet 300 3,000 1,500 750 15 Inferno's Gloves 187 Fluminis' Gloves 300 3,000 1,500 750 15 Inferno's Boots 188 Fluminis' Boots 600 4,000 2,000 1,000 20 Inferno's Armor 190 Fluminis' Armor 1,000 5,000 3,000 1,500 50 Inferno's Tights 190 Fluminis' Armor 1,000 5,000 3,000 1,500 50 Inferno's Garb 190 Fluminis' Armor 1,000 5,000 3,000 1,500 50 Inferno's Coat 190 Fluminis' Armor 1,000 5,000 3,000 1,500 50 Total Helmet + Gloves + Boots + 1 Armor piece 2,200 15,000 8,000 4,000 100 Reviac Set Lv 191 195 Best in Slot Reviac's Helmet 191 Inferno's Helmet 1,500 6,000 3,000 1,500 10 Reviac's Gloves 192 Inferno's Gloves 1,500 6,000 3,000 1,500 10 Reviac's Boots 193 Inferno's Boots 2,000 8,000 4,000 2,000 15 Reviac's Armor 195 Inferno's Armor 3,000 10,000 6,000 3,000 35 Reviac's Tights 195 Inferno's Tights 3,000 10,000 6,000 3,000 35 Reviac's Garb 195 Inferno's Garb 3,000 10,000 6,000 3,000 35 Reviac's Coat 195 Inferno's Coat 3,000 10,000 6,000 3,000 35 Total Helmet + Gloves + Boots + 1 Armor piece 8,000 30,000 16,000 8,000 70 Grand Total Full Journey (Nusy Fluminis Inferno Reviac) 11,200 45,000 24,000 12,000 100 70 Scales of Devildom and Devil Orbs Scales of Devildom needed for Inferno. Combine Refined Crystals with Black Scale pieces dropped by Stage 4 6 bosses. Devil Orbs needed for Reviac. Drop from Stage 6 bosses. A daily quest rewards a box containing either a Devil Orb or a Devil Orb Piece combine 10 pieces to make one Orb. Devildom Cloaks Three cloaks crafted from Devildom materials. Craft the White or Black cloak first one is required to make the Sand Dragon's Cloak . Enhanced using Dark Cubes available from the Cash Shop or purchasable with Luciad Medals from the Rondo Citadel NPC . White and Black cap at +10 ; Sand goes to +20 . White Dragon's Cloak Physical max +10 Black Dragon's Cloak Magical max +10 Sand Dragon's Cloak Hybrid max +20 Best White Dragon's Cloak Physical max +10 + P/M.Def P.Atk Ign.P.Def +0 10 1.0% 50 +1 15 1.5% 75 +2 20 2.0% 100 +3 30 2.5% 125 +4 40 3.0% 150 +5 55 4.0% 200 +6 70 5.0% 250 +7 90 6.0% 300 +8 110 7.0% 350 +9 130 8.0% 450 +10 150 10.0% 550 Black Dragon's Cloak Magical max +10 + P/M.Def M.Atk Ign.M.Def +0 10 1.0% 50 +1 15 1.5% 75 +2 20 2.0% 100 +3 30 2.5% 125 +4 40 3.0% 150 +5 55 4.0% 200 +6 70 5.0% 250 +7 90 6.0% 300 +8 110 7.0% 350 +9 130 8.0% 450 +10 150 10.0% 550 Sand Dragon's Cloak Hybrid Best max +20 + P/M.Def P.andM.Atk Pierce Crit.Pow +0 200 10.0% 2.5% 2 +1 210 10.0% 3.0% 3 +2 220 10.5% 3.5% 4 +3 230 10.5% 4.0% 5 +4 250 11.0% 4.5% 6 +5 280 11.0% 5.0% 7 +6 320 11.5% 5.5% 8 +7 370 11.5% 6.0% 9 +8 420 12.0% 6.5% 10 +9 470 12.0% 7.0% 11 +10 570 12.5% 7.5% 12 +11 670 13.0% 8.0% 13 +12 770 13.5% 8.5% 14 +13 870 14.0% 9.0% 15 +14 970 14.5% 9.5% 16 +15 1,070 15.0% 10.0% 17 +16 1,170 16.0% 11.0% 18 +17 1,270 17.0% 12.0% 19 +18 1,370 18.0% 13.0% 21 +19 1,470 19.0% 14.0% 23 +20 1,570 20.0% 15.0% 25 Cloak Crafting Materials Material White Dragon Black Dragon Sand Dragon Yushiva Essence 35 35 175 Soul Bead of White Dragon 15,000 15,000 15,000 Soul Bead of Black Dragon 3,000 3,000 3,000 Soul Bead of Sand Dragon 1,000 1,000 1,000 Refined Crystal of Devildom 500 500 500 White Steel 500 500 500 White Piece of Fabric 50 50 150 White Dragon's Scale 100 Black Dragon's Scale 100 Sand Dragon's Scale 100 White Pieces of Fabric: Stage 4 6 bosses. Dragon's Scales: Black Market NPCs. Job Type Note Cross-Class Upgrading Nusylite and Fluminis can be worn by all job types , allowing cross-class Parallel World upgrades (e.g. a War Kahuna wearing Berserker-exclusive Mach's Armor upgraded to Nusylite). Once upgraded to Inferno , equipment becomes job-type specific again plan which character does the upgrade before spending materials. RAPPELZ CODEX Fan-made community guide Not affiliated with Gala Lab"},{"title":"Pet Staging Guide","cat":"Guide","url":"guide/pet-staging/","text":"Pet Staging Guide RAPPELZ GUIDELINES Back to Home Back to Home Pet Staging How Staging Works Tame 2 of the same base pet and combine them that gives you a Stage 1. Combine 2 Stage 1s and you get a Stage 2. It always takes 2 pets of the same stage to make the next one. Starting out? All you need for your first Stage 1 is 2 base pets (called S0) of the same type. Tame them, then use the staging interface to combine them you'll need a Soul Catalyst, available from the Enchanter NPC (cheaper in HV). Each step up requires twice as many base pets. The table below shows how that adds up if you want to reach Stage 5: Target Stage What you combine Total base pets needed Stage 1 2 Base Pets (S0) 2 Stage 2 2 Stage 1 4 Stage 3 2 Stage 2 8 Stage 4 2 Stage 3 16 Stage 5 2 Stage 4 32 Full Breakdown to Stage 5 This shows how many pets of each stage you need to build a single Stage 5 from scratch: Stage 5 x1 Stage 4 x2 Stage 3 x4 Stage 2 x8 Stage 1 x16 Base Pet (S0) x32 Getting to Stage 5 requires 32 base pets in total Success Rates Staging is not guaranteed. Each attempt has a chance to fail. The chance depends on the pet type and gets lower at higher stages. Important: Only the pet in the material slot is lost on failure the pet in the main slot is kept. Always put your higher-leveled pet in the main slot so you don't lose it if the attempt fails. Bonus: Starting from Stage 3, there is a small chance of receiving a Joker even when the staging attempt fails. Stage Classic Soul Pet Epic Pet Stage 1 90% 45% 50% Stage 2 70% 30% 40% Stage 3 49% 25% 30% Stage 4 34% 17% 20% Stage 5 24% 12% 10% Additional Bonuses You can increase the success rate by: Bonus Source Rate Added 1 Creature Level +0.125% Advanced Soul Catalyst +10% Joker +30% Creature Level matters: The combined level of both pets is what counts. For example, two pets at level 40 (40+40 = 80) gives the same bonus as one at level 70 and one at level 10 (70+10 = 80). 100% Success Rate Requirements To guarantee a successful stage, you need the right combination of creature levels and optional items. Both the combined level of the two pets and the additional item used determines whether you hit 100%. Classic Pets Stage Creature Level (each) Additional Item Stage 1 40 + 40 None Stage 2 120 + 120 None Stage 3 164 + 164 Advanced Soul Catalyst 204 + 204 None Stage 4 144 + 144 Joker Stage 5 184 + 184 Joker Soul Pets Stage Creature Level (each) Additional Item Stage 1 180 + 180 Advanced Soul Catalyst 220 + 220 None Stage 2 160 + 160 Joker Stage 3 180 + 180 Joker Stage 4 212 + 212 Joker Stage 5 Not achievable max is 220+220 + Joker at 97% Epic Pets Stage Creature Level (each) Additional Item Stage 1 160 + 160 Advanced Soul Catalyst 200 + 200 None Stage 2 120 + 120 Joker 200 + 200 Advanced Soul Catalyst Stage 3 160 + 160 Joker Stage 4 200 + 200 Joker Stage 5 Not achievable max is 220+220 + Joker at 95% Important: When staging, only the combined creature level of both pets counts. The pets do not need to be at equal levels 40+40 gives the same result as 70+10. The table above shows equal-level examples for simplicity. Source Original reference table used for this guide: Thanks to Gazi and LessHerpMoreDerp for providing the data. RAPPELZ GUIDELINES - Fan-made community guide Not affiliated with Gala Lab or any official publisher Content is community-sourced. Contribute corrections via the Discord."}];
